Beavis has a dream in which he is the Scrooge-like manager there and Principal McVicker is one of his employees. Beavis is visited by Butt-head, the Ghosts of Christmas Past, Present and Future â€“ (presumably) Marley, Tom Anderson, Mr. Van Driessen and Coach Buzzcut respectively â€“ while trying to watch a porno on VHS.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Beavis and Butthead/S06/Beavis.and.Butthead.S06E08.Stewart.Is.Missing.mkv
items.summary:
Part 2 of the 1995 Christmas Special. In this parody of "It's A Wonderful Life", the duo are visited by his guardian angel, who shows Butt-Head that everyone in Highland would have had a better life if he had not been born. In the version of Highland in which Butt-Head had not been born, Anderson's yard is in a much better condition, Burger World has more customers and McVicker still has his hair. Beavis and Stewart are volunteers at a homeless shelter.

videos: Run-DMC - "Christmas in Hollis"
items.title: It's a Miserable Life

items.summary: After a three week absence from school, the principal's office calls 'the house' to learn the whereabouts of the boys...only to learn that they are dead. In the teachers' lounge at Highland High, Mr. Van Driessen wants to mourn Beavis and Butt-head by "celebrating their lives;" Principal McVicker wants to cash in on the tragedy by holding a fundraiser for the school; Buzzcut is just happy they're dead. Flashbacks a-plenty as the supporting cast recalls their fond memories of Beavis and Butt-head.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x01 - Pilot.mkv
items.summary: Film critic Jay Sherman falls in love with actress Valerie Fox.  Jay's family and friends worry that Valerie is using him to get a good movie review.  Does she truly care for him?
items.title: Pilot

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x02 - Marty's First Date.mkv
items.summary: Marty invites his Jay to career day at his school where Marty develops a crush on a Cuban girl named Carmen. They go on a date but when Carmen decides to fly back to Cuba, Marty follows her and Jay must get his son back.
items.title: Marty's First Date

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x03 - Dial 'M' For Mother.mkv
items.summary: Jay is considered to be one of the most unpopular men on Earth (ranking even worse than Adolph Hitler) so Duke attempts to spruce up the show to get more people interested. When this doesn't work, Jay decides to soften his image by going on the "Geraldo Show" with his mother but Jay gets an even worse reputation when his mother embarrasses him to the point where he tells her to "shut up".
items.title: Dial 'M' For Mother

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x04 - Miserable.mkv
items.summary: Jay, noticing everyone in New York has a fiancee except him, begins to feel unloved. Things change when he goes to review the movie, Indecent Proposal II, and falls in love with the projectionist screening the movie. They arrange a date at her house where she is revealed to have an obsession with Jay to the point where she kidnaps him and ties him to a bed holding him hostage.
items.title: Miserable

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x05 - A Little Deb Will Do You.mkv
items.summary: Eleanor is determined to have her daughter, Margo, attend the annual debutantes ball as it is a tradition in her family. When Margo is reluctantly forced into it, Jay decides to accompany her. Meanwhile, Jay competes in his time slot against children's idol Humphrey the Hippo.
items.title: A Little Deb Will Do You

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x06 - Eyes on the Prize.mkv
items.summary: Jay celebrates his 1000th episode but the episode is less than successful. Ratings get worse so Jay seeks image consultant, Adolph Hitmaker, for advice. The advice is unsuccessful and Jay is fired. Jay gets a new job on a show which teaches English for cab drivers but Jay is unhappy so he decides to win himself another Pulitzer Prize.
items.title: Eyes on the Prize

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x07 - Every Doris Has Her Day.mkv
items.summary: Jay befriends his make-up lady Doris after they attend a musical adaptation of The Hunchback of Notre Dame, and thinks that she may be the mother who gave him up for adoption years ago.
items.title: Every Doris Has Her Day

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x08 - Marathon Mensch.mkv
items.summary: When the studio catches fire during Jay's show, he collapses and must be rescued from the fire by Doris. When the news reports Jay's being rescued, he gets a reputation as being a wimp so he tries to prove his manliness by running in the New York marathon which tends to be more tiresome than it seems.
items.title: Marathon Mensch

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x09 - L.A. Jay.mkv
items.summary: Jay is offered to write the screenplay for a new movie, Ghostchasers III, so he takes a break from his show to go to L.A. to write the new movie and experience Hollywood life but the movie producer isn't satisfied with Jay's script.
items.title: L.A. Jay

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x10 - Dr. Jay.mkv
items.summary: Jay's boss, Duke, has just made a new invention, "Phillips-o-Vision" which alters movies to make them more "like-able". Jay is disgusted with Duke's invention but when Duke is discovered to have a fatal disease, Jay must find a cure for Duke's ailment.
items.title: Dr. Jay

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x11 - A Day at the Races and a Night at the Opera.mkv
items.summary: After Marty fails to win an event at his school field day, he is feeling very low so Jay tries to improve his self-confidence by getting him interested in playing guitar and putting him in the school talent show. Meanwhile, Them Magazine names Jay "the wittiest man alive" so Duke offers to pay everyone who doesn't laugh at Jay's show $100 which doesn't go over very well.
items.title: A Day at the Races and a Night at the Opera
items.titleSort: Day at the Races and a Night at the Opera

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x12 - Uneasy Rider.mkv
items.summary: After refusing to plug chewing tobacco on his show, Jay quits his job and becomes a truck driver.
items.title: Uneasy Rider

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S01/The Critic - 1x13 - A Pig-Boy and His Dog.mkv
items.summary: "A Pig-Boy and His Dog" is the 13th episode of The Critic. This was the final episode to air on ABC.
items.title: A Pig-Boy and His Dog

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S02/The Critic - 2x01 - Sherman, Woman and Child.mkv
items.summary: Jay's ratings are not doing very well and Duke is about to fire him so Jay is feeling depressed. His feelings become better when he meets a new girlfriend named Alice and her daughter Penny. Alice gives Jay tips on how to improve his show and her advice works. Jay wants to get to know Alice better but discovers she has a boyfriend whom she wants to reject but can't.
items.title: Sherman, Woman and Child

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S02/The Critic - 2x02 - Siskel & Ebert & Jay & Alice.mkv
items.summary: After Jay attends the Academy Awards, Gene Siskel and Roger Ebert break up and each rope Jay to be their new partner.
items.title: Siskel & Ebert & Jay & Alice

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S02/The Critic - 2x03 - Lady Hawke.mkv
items.summary: When Jeremy Hawke's sister, Olivia Newton Hawke, visits New York, Jay meets her and is smitten with her which puts his relationship with Alice on the line when she begins to feel left out. So Jay then must decide who he really loves.
items.title: Lady Hawke

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S02/The Critic - 2x04 - A Song for Margo.mkv
items.summary: Margo gets a new neighbor, Johnny Wrath, who is the lead singer in the rock group, "Nuns in a Blender". Margo falls in love with him but doesn't feel the relationship is right when she finds him with another girl. Meanwhile Alice tries to find a suitable preschool for Penny.
items.title: A Song for Margo

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S02/The Critic - 2x05 - From Chunk to Hunk.mkv
items.summary: Jay and Marty begin to feel a little big so they enroll in a weight loss camp. Marty loses a remarkable amount of weight which makes him feel more self- confident but when he is placed as the star in a school play, he doesn't feel his skinny self is right for him. Meanwhile, Jay receives a death threat from Belgian actor Jean Paul Le Pope whose movie he panned.
items.title: From Chunk to Hunk

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S02/The Critic - 2x06 - All the Duke's Men.mkv
items.summary: When Jay helps Marty become class president, Duke decides to have Jay help him become US President.
items.title: All the Duke's Men

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S02/The Critic - 2x07 - Sherman of Arabia.mkv
items.summary: At Marty's slumber party, Jay is asked to tell his story in which he got caught up in the Gulf War. Jay tells how he was attending an Iraqi film festival and eventually was thrown in jail where he escaped and lead a troop of men across the desert.
items.title: Sherman of Arabia

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S02/The Critic - 2x08 - Frankie and Ellie Get Lost.mkv
items.summary: Franklin and Eleanor celebrate their 40th anniversary by going on vacation but the plane crashes and Franklin and Eleanor find themselves marooned on an island. Back in New York, Margo and Jay find out about their disappearance and discover they have willed Jay their entire fortune which Jay decides to put to use by cleaning up New York.
items.title: Frankie and Ellie Get Lost

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S02/The Critic - 2x09 - Dukerella.mkv
items.summary: Alice's sister, Miranda, comes to visit them which Alice is not comfortable with. Miranda must find work in New York so she joins "Mattress in an Hour" delivering mattresses. When everybody attends a party held by Duke, Miranda falls in love with Duke but is shy because of a wrinkle. She runs out on Duke at midnight and Duke must find the woman who fits her slipper. When it turns out to be Doris, Jay must get Duke and Miranda reunited.
items.title: Dukerella

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Critic/S02/The Critic - 2x10 - I Can't Believe It's a Clip Show.mkv
items.summary: Jay is hosting his 10th anniversary show held at Carnegie Hall where he showcases a number of movie clips from old episodes such as Jurassic Park 2, Every Which Way but Lucid, and Rabbi P.I. The show is later held hostage by a number of terrorists who threaten to blow the place up with a bomb tied to Jay's waist. Fortunately, everybody is eventually rescued by Milton Berle.
items.title: I Can't Believe It's a Clip Show
items.titleSort: I Can't Believe It's a Clip Show

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 01 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Brilliant but bored high school student Light Yagami suddenly finds himself holding the power of life and death in his handsâ€”the power of the Death Note. He decides to rid the world of evilâ€”by killing off criminals one by one. When the murders start to pile up, genius detective L is on the case, and an epic battle of wits unfolds.
items.title: Rebirth

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 02 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: While the worldâ€™s criminals continue to drop dead, L meets by computer with representatives from various nations. He requests that a task force be set up in Japan, under the direction of none other than Soichiro Yagami, Lightâ€™s father.
items.title: Confrontation

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 03 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Ryuk informs Light that he's being followed and asks Light if he wants to make a trade for his own Shinigami eyes. But at what cost?
items.title: Dealings

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 04 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Lightâ€”now known to the world as Kiraâ€”tests the Death Note to understand the scope of its powers by killing off six convicts in various waysâ€”and confirms he can control his victimsâ€™ actions before they die.
items.title: Pursuit

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 05 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: After finding the true identity of his follower, Light uses him to deal a major blow to the rest of his enemies.
items.title: Tactics

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 06 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Light meets a woman at the Police Department with an urgent message for the Kira task force. As son of the chief investigator, Light listens to her story, and is startled to discover she may have information that could lead to his arrest.
items.title: Unraveling

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 07 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Light uses the Death Note to try to get rid of the woman who could get him captured, and is shocked when it doesnâ€™t work. Realizing she must have given him an alias, heâ€™s only got minutes to find out her real name before she tells her story to the task force.
items.title: Overcast

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 08 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: L insists on setting up bugs and cameras in the homes of Chief Yagami and Deputy Director Kitamuraâ€”whom Raye Penber was tracking. But Light is a step ahead as usualâ€”he knows heâ€™s being watched.
items.title: Glare

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 09 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: The murders continue, and L grows suspicious of Lightâ€™s too-perfect behavior and decides to investigate him on his own. In order to get closer to Light, L enrolls at the same university and reveals himself to be L.
items.title: Encounter

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 10 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: L's suspicion of Light deepens, compelling him to invite Light into the investigation. But then a phone call alerts them that Soichiro Yagami has suffered a heart attack!
items.title: Doubt

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 11 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: As predicted on the tapes sent to Sakura TV, news anchors and commentators who expressed doubt about Kira die one by one. On further investigation, L concludes that this Kira is not the originalâ€”there's a second Kira!
items.title: Assault

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 12 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: With a second Kira now on the loose, L asks Light to join the task force and pose as the real Kira in order to catch the copycat. Light agrees, hoping to divert suspicion from himself. To his surprise, this new Kira has a special ability even Light lacksâ€¦
items.title: Love

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 13 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Light goes to Aoyama to discover the identity of the second Kira before L becomes more suspicious. But Misa Amane, the new Kira, uses her unusual gift to find Light before he finds her.
items.title: Confession

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 14 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Light and Misa show each other their Death Notes, and Light asks Misa to have her shinigami Rem get rid of L. But Misa asks something of Light in returnâ€”to fall in love with her!
items.title: Friend

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 15 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Evidence turns up that points to Misa Amane as the second Kira. In an effort to spare her, Rem forces Misa to forfeit her ownership of the Death Note.
items.title: Wager

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 16 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Misa is in confinement, though her memories of the Death Note have been completely wiped away. When Light is confined as well, the murders stop and suspicion of Light grows stronger. Then suddenly, the killings resume.
items.title: Decision

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 17 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: After fifty days of confinement the killings continue, and Misa and Light are released. But L has devised a plan to ensure no more murders occur, and has Light's father, Soichiro, take the two for a ride that may be their last.
items.title: Execution

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 18 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Though L is still suspicious, Light and Misa, their memories of being Kira wiped clean, return to headquarters, where Light notices a strange connection between the recent Kira killings and the Yotsuba Group.
items.title: Ally

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 19 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Matsuda, the task force member assigned to watch Misa, is eager to distinguish himself, and while on a job with Misa, he decides to do a little snooping on his own at the Yotsuba Groupâ€™s Tokyo headquarters.
items.title: Matsuda

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 20 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: L's team discovers that the Yotsuba Group meet in secret to discuss the elimination of individuals who are troublesome to their company, and concludes that Kira must be one of the eight executives. Can Light posing as L ferret out the right one?
items.title: Makeshift

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 21 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: The Task Force uses Misa as a way to get closer to the Yotsuba corporation. But things get complicated when Rem tries to communicate with her.
items.title: Performance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 22 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Thanks to Misa, the Task Force now knows the identity of the new Kira and L plans an elaborate scheme to smoke him out of hiding.
items.title: Guidance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 23 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: L, Light and Misa watch from the investigation team building and wonder who he is talking to. L wonders if Higuchi is talking to a shinigami. Rem convinces Higuchi to go to the station, but she has her own selfish motives for doing so.
items.title: Frenzy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 24 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: While Higuchi is finally captured, Light inadvertently regains his memories as Kira.
items.title: Revival

items.summary: Light, his memory recovered, orders Misa to begin killing after Higuchi dies. The Shinigami Rem realizes that everything is going according to Light's plan, and that L will arrest Misa as Kira-unless Rem acts quickly.
items.title: Silence

items.summary: After L's death, the world needs a new great detective. Is Wammy's house, where L comes from, able to find a new super detective who can complete L's hunt for Kira?
items.title: Renewal

items.summary: A new investigator steps forward-Near, a central figure in the SPK, an organization that is trying to catch Kira without relying on L. Near is aware of the existence of the Death Notes and wants to get his hands on one.
items.title: Abduction

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 28 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Light, acting as L, reveals to Near that his sister Sayu has been kidnapped by someone wanting to trade her for the Death Note. Near finds out that the trade will happen in Los Angeles and promises to help, while secretly planning to steal the Death Note and capture Kira.
items.title: Impatience

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 29 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Mortified over allowing the Death Note to fall into Mello's hands in order to save his daughter, Soichiro puts himself into harm's way in order to get it back.
items.title: Father

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 30 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Mello busts into SPK headquarters to retrieve a photograph of himself to make sure he won't be killed by Kira. In exchange for Near giving him the picture, Mello drops an important hint about the Death Notes: some of the rules are fake.
items.title: Justice

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 31 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Near contacts the Japanese task force and determines that Kira is among their members. He asks for insider information, and Aizawa, beginning to doubt Light, responds. Near suspects that the new L is really Light Yagami and that Light is Kira.
items.title: Transfer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 32 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Star newscaster Kiyomi Takada becomes Kira's spokesperson to the world, after Demegawa is deleted by Mikami, and she just so happens to have been Light's girlfriend in college. Aizawa's suspicions about Light grow.
items.title: Selection

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 33 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Near goes to Japan, allegedly as bait for Kira. Following Light's instructions, Takada asks Mikami to send her five pages of the Death Note. She tells him that he will continue his work in a fake book made to look like the real one.
items.title: Scorn

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 34 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Aizawa figures out what's going on and tells Near, who already knows about the notes. Near instructs Aizawa to continue watching Light, and then puts in motion a plan to separate Misa from Light.
items.title: Vigilance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 35 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Light and Near agree upon a meeting place for the final confrontation. A key player is kidnapped and the end results are shocking.
items.title: Malice

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 36 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: The Japanese Task Force and the SPK finally meet at YellowBox Warehouse on January 28th. However, a third party has come to the warehouse as well, on Kira's orders to kill everyone else there.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Death Note/Death Note - 37 (GamePersia).mkv
items.summary: Though Mikami has written all the investigators' names in the Death Note, a minute passes and everyone is still alive. Near seizes Mikami's Death Note, and all is at last revealed.
items.title: New World

items.summary: In the series premiere, we find the Funnie family have moved from Bloatsburg and are just arriving at their new home in the town of Bluffington. 11 year old Doug Funnie writes his thoughts in his journal and worries he won't be able to make any friends. On a search to find food for his Mom (Theda), Dad (Phil) and sister (Judy), Doug meets his next door neighbour Mr. Dink. He shows Doug a video about Bluffington and introduces him to the popular hangout fast food restaurant called The Honker Burger. When Doug gets to the hangout, he meets Skeeter Valentine who befriends him right away. Doug also meets Patti Mayonnaise and right away, has a secret crush on her. items.title: Plans for Departure

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragonball Z/S01/DBZ - 038 - Nursing Wounds.mkv
items.summary: Goku, Krillin, and Gohan prepare for the return of the Saiyans. Meanwhile, Bulma and Mr. Popo search for a second spaceship capable of transporting her to Planet Namek.
items.title: Nursing Wounds

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragonball Z/S01/DBZ - 039 - Friends or Foes.mkv
items.summary: Gohan, Bulma, and Krillin blast off for Planet Namek in search of the magic Dragon Balls, but their journey quickly turns chaotic when they encounter a bizarre situation in the vacuum of space!
items.title: Friends or Foes?

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 10 The Dragon Balls are Stolen!.mkv
items.summary: Goku and the others aim for the final Dragon Ball! However, their Dragon Balls are stolen by Pilaf and his underlings, who are plotting to use the Dragon Balls to take over the world!! Wanting to have his wish granted by Shen Long, Yamcha once again ends up helping Bulma and the others in order to obtain the Dragon Balls. In order to get the Dragon Balls back, Goku and the others invade Pilafâ€™s secret base. But they are all caught by the ingenious trap set by Pilaf. Gokuâ€™s Four-Star Ball is in danger!!
items.title: The Dragon Balls are Stolen!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 11 The Penalty is Pinball.mkv
items.summary: After being put to sleep by sleeping gas, Goku and the others have the Four-Star Ball stolen from them! Pilaf finally has all seven Dragon Balls, and he attempts to call forth Shen Long!! In order to stop Pilafâ€™s scheme, Goku uses the Kamehameha to open a hole in the wall of the room that they are imprisoned in! As Puâ€™er and Oolong transform into bats and head out the hole to take back the Dragon Balls, Shen Long is finally summoned! Will the world become Pilafâ€™sâ€¦?!
items.title: The Penalty is Pinball

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 12 A Wish to the Eternal Dragon.mkv
items.summary: Shen Long finally appears! Pilaf tries to say his wish, in order to rule the world!! Because Oolong said his wish of â€œGive me a girlâ€™s pantiesâ€ a moment sooner, his wish ended up being granted! With the wish granted, Shen Long returns again to the Dragon Balls, and they scatter to the four winds. Enraged, Pilaf imprisons Goku and the others in a room covered in fortified glass and iron plates, intending to kill them with the sunâ€™s hot rays, butâ€¦?!
items.title: A Wish to the Eternal Dragon

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 13 The Legend of Goku.mkv
items.summary: Goku and the others have been captured once again by Pilaf. That night, Goku looks at the full moon, and suddenly turns wild and starts transforming into an Oozaru!! He smashes the prison that they are imprisoned in, and Yamcha and the rest manage to escape, but having lost his reason, Goku continues to rampage!! Yamcha then cuts off Gokuâ€™s weakness, his tail! Goku wakes up after returning to normal. The party promises to reunite, and the Dragon Team splits up.
items.title: The Legend of Goku

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 14 Goku's Rival.mkv
items.summary: Done with collecting the Dragon Balls, Goku heads to the Turtle Hermitâ€™s place to receive training! However, in order to become the Turtle Hermitâ€™s pupil, the fee is to bring a pichi-pichi gal!! At the same time, a person comes from across the sea. The boy, who calls himself Kuririn, came in order to become the Turtle Hermitâ€™s pupil, just like Goku! In order to be received as a pupil, Kuririn presents a large stash of porn magazines that he brought. Will he manage to safely become a pupilâ€¦?!
items.title: Goku's Rival

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 15 Look Out for Launch.mkv
items.summary: Goku and Kuririn set out in search of a pichi-pichi gal, the fee for becoming a pupil of the Turtle Hermit. Saving Lunch, a girl who was pursued by the police, they immediately bring her to the Turtle Hermitâ€™s place! Having passed the test, Goku and Kuririn are recognized as the Turtle Hermitâ€™s pupils!! But it turns out that Lunch is an incredibly peculiar girl with two personalities, and becomes either violent or peaceful each time she sneezes!!
items.title: Look Out for Launch

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 16 Find That Stone!.mkv
items.summary: Moving to a large island, the Turtle Hermit begins the training. First, in order to learn Goku and Kuririnâ€™s ability, he measures how fast they can run 100 meters. The two look promising, and the Turtle Hermit gives them some training before dinner. Itâ€™s a great trial where he throws a stone with the â€œturtleâ€ mark on it into the jungle, then tells the two to find it! The person who doesnâ€™t manage to find it will go without dinner! Goku and Kuririn take this severe training in earnest!! The sly Kuririn seizes victory in this contest!
items.title: Find That Stone!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 17 Milk Delivery.mkv
items.summary: The basic training finally begins! To start off, Goku and Kuririn are given milk delivery as their early morning training! Carrying the milk boxes, they do things like skip and zig-zag around rows of trees!! Furthermore, they climb stone stairs that rise high into the air, cross over a valley on a large tree, cross through a desert of quicksand and a raging river while keeping their balance, and get chased by dinosaurs as a bonus! This is their ultra-hard milk delivery training that surpasses ordinary knowledge!!
items.title: Milk Delivery

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 18 The Turtle Hermit Way.mkv
items.summary: With their early morning training over, they continue on to their morning training. In order to strengthen their arms and legs, they train by plowing a field barehanded! After breakfast itâ€™s study time!! After lunch, they take an afternoon nap until 1:30. During the afternoon they help out with construction work. Itâ€™s training where they sweat, toughen their muscles, and even receive a part-time job salary! Furthermore, they carry themselves through rough training to toughen their reflexes, swimming ten laps around a lake while being chased by sharks and dodging the frenzied attacks of bees, to finally end a full day of training!
items.title: The Turtle Hermit Way

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 19 The Tournament Begins.mkv
items.summary: Goku and Kuririn continue their training by wearing 40 kg shells on their back! The two are aiming for the Tenkaichi Budokai, which opens in a month!! The day before the tournament, the Turtle Hermit takes them to the island where it will be held! At the tournament registration area, Goku reunites with Yamcha, Bulma, Oolong, and Puâ€™er. Goku is delighted when he learns that Yamcha is also participating! The next day, the Tenkaichi Budokai is at last decided!!
items.title: The Tournament Begins

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 20 Elimination Round.mkv
items.summary: The Tenkaichi Budokai is held once every five years! A mere eight people are able to participate in the tournamentâ€™s main event! The preliminaries to select those eight people are divided up into four blocks!! Goku and Kuririn fully display the results of the harsh training that they received from the Turtle Hermit!! Tossing a veteran to his defeat, Goku splendidly gains the right to participate in the main event! Whatâ€™s more, Yamcha also advances well, and wins his ticket to the Tenkaichi Budokai main event!!
items.title: Elimination Round

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 21 Smells Like Trouble.mkv
items.summary: The first round of the Tenkaichi Budokai main event is Kuririn vs. Bacterian! Bacterian is a formidable opponent who uses his filth as a weapon, with his foul smell paralyzing his opponents. With bad breath, farts, and the like, he assaults Kuririn with foul-smelling attacks!! The helpless Kuririn is finally downed!! At that time, Kuririn awakens from this nightmare of smells when Goku tells him â€œYou donâ€™t have a nose!â€ Launching a fierce counterattack against Bacterian, Kuririn breaks through the first round!
items.title: Smells Like Trouble

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 22 Quarterfinals Begin.mkv
items.summary: Itâ€™s the second match, Yamcha vs Jackie Chun! The mysterious old man Jackie Chun defies Yamchaâ€™s rapid attacks, and breaks through even his special attack, the Roga fufu-ken (Wolf Fang Gale Fist)!! Furthermore, Jackie seizes victory by raising a wind with a swing of his left hand, blowing Yamcha out of bounds! In the third match, the serious Namu is assaulted by Ran-Fanâ€™s sex appeal strategy!! But Namu achieves a turnabout victory when he defeats Ran-Fan with a single blow after freeing himself from distracting thoughts!
items.title: Quarterfinals Begin

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 23 Monster Beast Giran.mkv
items.summary: At last itâ€™s Gokuâ€™s turn! The one facing Goku in the fourth match was the powerful opponent Giran!! Goku is knocked around by Giranâ€™s stream of unfair attacks! Giran traps Goku in the rubbery Guru-Guru Gum that he shoots from his mouth!! Goku is in an absolutely desperate pinch! Just as he is about to be thrown out of the ring, his chopped-off tail suddenly grows back, and his power multiplies! Seeing this, Giran surrenders!!
items.title: Monster Beast Giran

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 24 Krillin's Frantic Attack!.mkv
items.summary: The fifth match is the semi-finals fight, Kuririn vs. Jackie Chun. Kuririn and Jackieâ€™s battle unfolds at ultra-fast speed that the eye canâ€™t follow!! The spectators who came to watch the Tenkaichi Budokai are extremely excited by the pairâ€™s high level battle!! Kuririn puts up a good fight against Jackie, but he rushes to win! Because of this, he is hit by Jackieâ€™s karate chops after Jackie goes around behind his back, and is downed!! Sadly, Kuririn is defeated during the semi-finals.
items.title: Krillin's Frantic Attack!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 25 Danger From Above.mkv
items.summary: The sixth match is Goku and Namuâ€™s semi-finals fight. Goku attacks Namu by imitating the Zanzouken that Jackie displayed during his fight with Kuririn. Namu skillfully dodges this attack! Namu attempts to finish Goku off with his special attack, the Tenku pekeji-ken! Goku is hit by the attack and downed, but revives right before the count of ten! Namu further comes out him with the Super Tenku pekeji-ken, but Goku breaks through the technique. Goku then advances to the finals!
items.title: Danger From Above

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 26 The Grand Finals.mkv
items.summary: The finals for the 21st Tenkaichi Budokai have been decided! Goku is knocked out of bounds by Jackie. But he spins his tail like a propeller and comes back! Goku and Jackie at last put forth their best. The two fire a Kamehameha at the same time!! Gokuâ€™s Kamehameha evenly matches Jackieâ€™s, and knocks it back!! Demonstrating a back-and-forth display of such attacks as the Zanzouken, the Suiken, and the Saruken, their red-hot battle continues!
items.title: The Grand Finals

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 27 Number One Under the Moon.mkv
items.summary: Becoming serious against Goku, Jackie uses the Yoiko Min-Min Ken! Goku enters a deep sleep. He somehow manages to escape this pinch, but he is assaulted by Jackieâ€™s special attack, the Bankoku-Bikkuri-Sho! With a shockwave like an electric current running up his entire body, Goku is robbed of the ability to move. But just as heâ€™s about to surrender, his eyes catch sight of the full moon! Against Goku, who has transformed into an Oozaru once again, Jackie fires an extra-large Kamehameha!! What is Gokuâ€™s fateâ€¦?!
items.title: Number One Under the Moon?

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 28 The Final Blow.mkv
items.summary: Jackie blew away the moon, guarding against Goku ever becoming an Oozaru again!! At the same time, Goku returns to his normal form, and the match is restarted. With their energy rapidly falling from exhaustion and hunger, the two muster the last of their power, and their clash unfolds. Having received slightly less damage, Jackie declares that he has won the championship, and he achieves victory. items.summary: Dracula Man, the first opponent, challenges Kuririn! Kuririn is filled with confidence, but he gets bitten in the head by Dracula Man and has his blood sucked! They blow Dracula Man away with the things a vampire hates, garlic and the crucifix! Moving on, they pass the baton to Yamcha, but the next opponent is Mr. Invisible, an invisible man of all things!!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 71 Deadly Battle.mkv
items.summary: Yamcha has a tough battle with an undetectable invisible man as his opponent! Goku returns after having been instructed by Kuririn to bring the Turtle Hermit and Bulma. Kuririn pulls down Bulmaâ€™s clothes when the timing is right, and blood shoots from the Turtle Hermitâ€™s nose once he sees Bulmaâ€™s chest! Bathed in this nosebleed, the invisible manâ€™s form appears, and he is defeated by Yamcha. Kuririnâ€™s strategy wins! Meanwhile, the battleground is moved to the â€œDemons' Toiletâ€!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 72 Goku's Turn.mkv

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 73 The Devilmite Beam.mkv

items.summary: Grabbing onto Gokuâ€™s tail, the fox mask man knocks Goku around! But then Gokuâ€™s tail comes off!! items.titleSort: True Colors of the Masked Man

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 77 Pilaf's Tactics.mkv

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 78 The Eternal Dragon Rises.mkv
items.summary: Having collected the seven Dragon Balls, Goku returns to Karin Tower with Upa. Then in response to Gokuâ€™s summons, Shen Long appears once again! items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 80 Goku vs. Sky Dragon.mkv

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 82 he Rampage of InoShikaCho.mkv
items.summary: Goku sees the two martial artists Tenshinhan and Chiaotzu defeat the monster Inoshikacho, whose rampages had plagued the villagers. items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 83 Which Way to Papaya Island.mkv
items.summary: Three years have passed since Goku set out on his training journey. One day, Goku rescues the fox boy Konkichi, who was being pursued by an evil group. items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 85 Preliminary Peril.mkv

items.summary: Gokuâ€™s match against King Chapa begins! items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 89 Full-Moon Vengeance.mkv

However, Tenshinhan enters and stops him, vowing that he will defeat Goku in their match!!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 92 Goku Enters the Ring.mkv
items.summary: Gokuâ€™s turn has come at last! His opponent is the popular action star, contestant Panputto! items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 93 Tien Shinhan vs. Jackie Chun.mkv

Tenshinhanâ€™s heart has begun to gradually turn. At the tournament grounds, Goku and Kuririnâ€™s very first fight has begun! The two fight at full force, not holding back!!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 97 Final Match Goku vs. Tien.mkv

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 100 The Spirit Cannon.mkv

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 109 Goku vs. King Piccolo.mkv

The Turtle Hermit finds himself between a rock and a hard place as he quests for the Three-Star ball.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 110 Piccolo Closes In.mkv

As the Turtle Hermit and others continue their pursuit of the Dragon Balls, it becomes clear that the trail leads to the dark forces of Piccolo Daimao and judgment day for our heroes.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 111 Roshi's Gambit.mkv

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 112 King Piccolo's Wish.mkv

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 113 Siege on Chow Castle.mkv

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 114 Conquest and Power.mkv
items.summary: Goku's reunion with Karin is filled with hope and disappointment as the hero receives shocking news! Meanwhile Piccolo Daimao attempts to force the King's obedience through a horrific display of brutality towards his kingdom and subjects as Tenshinhan prepares for the long journey to learn the secret of the Mafuba.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 115 Awaken Darkness.mkv

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 116 A Taste of Destiny.mkv

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 117 The Ultimate Sacrifice.mkv
