Meanwhile Goku and Yajirobe return to Karin Tower where Goku discovers his new powers and is given another Kinto'un. Can Goku reach Piccolo Daimao before Tenshinhan sacrifices himself?
items.title: The Ultimate Sacrifice

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 118 Prelude to Vengeance.mkv
items.summary: Piccolo Daimao has declared annihilation of the world, one sector at a time. First up, Metro West, home of Bulma's parents. Tenshinhan, having mastered the Mafuba, prepares to fight Piccolo Daimao, but a new menace threatens all. Goku race to offer aid, but will it be too late?
items.title: Prelude to Vengeance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 119 Battle Cry.mkv
items.summary: There's a new beast in town and his name is Drum. Tenshinhan must go through him before he can fight Piccolo Daimao. The problem is, Drum moves faster than Tenshinhan's eyes - all three of them! Goku is on his way, but will he arrive in time to save the day?
items.title: Battle Cry

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 120 Goku Strikes Back.mkv
items.summary: Goku is back to face Piccolo Daimao, and not a moment too soon! As Tenshinhan and the rest of the resistance endure their most desperate hour, only Goku stands between Piccolo Daimao and the destruction of Metro West. It's more than just a rematch, it's the battle to save the world!
items.title: Goku Strikes Back

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 121 The Biggest Crisis.mkv
items.summary: Piccolo Daimao puts all of Metro West on edge when he invades the King's Castle, but Goku is not about to let him take over without a fight. While Tenshinhan watches from the sidelines, the young warrior takes it on the chin and refuses to go down. It's a fierce battle but even Goku has his limits. How much can he take?
items.title: The Biggest Crisis

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 122 Final Showdown.mkv
items.summary: The fierce battle between Goku and Piccolo Daimao continues, but Piccolo gains the advantage when he breaks Goku down limb by limb. To make matters worse, Tenshinhan is used as a pawn in the battle. Goku is forced to make an awful choice. Will he surrender to Piccolo Daimao and save his friend or choose to fight and risk his own life?
items.title: Final Showdown

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 123 Lost and Found.mkv
items.summary: With Piccolo Daimao's reign of terror at an end, Goku has time to mend his wounds. As he heals he learns that there may be a way to revive his lost friends - face to face meeting with the creator of the Dragon Balls! The one problem is that the only way to get to the mysterious God is by using his Nyoi-bo, and it has gone missing!
items.title: Lost and Found

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 124 Temple Above the Clouds.mkv
items.summary: Goku finds his lost Nyoi-bo and uses it to climb to God's temple in the sky. The only problem is that when he arrives he must face off against God's assistant Mr. Popo in a test of strength. Does Goku have what it takes to pass this test and earn a meeting with the mysterious God?
items.title: Temple Above the Clouds

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 125 Earth's Guardian Emerges.mkv
items.summary: The moment has arrived for Goku to come face to face with the amazing God, Guardian of Earth! But even the wise Karin could not prepare Goku for what he will see when the mysterious Guardian emerges!
items.title: Earth's Guardian Emerges

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 126 Eternal Dragon Resurrected.mkv
items.summary: After Goku mistakes God for the villainous Piccolo Daimao it is time for the young warrior to begin his grueling three year training for the next Tenkaichi Budokai. In exchange for Goku's promise God agrees to revive the Eternal Dragon!
items.title: Eternal Dragon Resurrected

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 127 Quicker than Lightning.mkv
items.summary: Goku's first task under his new teacher is a death-defying mission to the top of Mount Thunder to fetch the legendary Holy Crown. But the mystical artifact has a deadly secret! Goku will have to be quicker than lightning to accomplish this task - alive!
items.title: Quicker than Lightning

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 128 Secret of the Woods.mkv
items.summary: Continuing his training, Goku follows Mr. Popo's instruction and enters the deep, dark woods. While searching for a worthy sparring partner, Goku stumbles across a surprising discovery hidden deep within the secluded labyrinth - and finds help a most unexpected way!
items.title: Secret of the Woods

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 129 The Time Room.mkv
items.summary: Goku journeys through time, where he meets a young Muten Roshi! But Roshi has a problem of his own - his arch rival, Shen! While the two rivals battle for the affections of the same girl, Goku attempts a new power with the help of Mutaito.
items.title: The Time Room

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 130 Goku's Doll.mkv
items.summary: "Be careful what you wish for. You just might get it!" Goku learns this lesson the hard way when he asks Mr. Popo for the ultimate sparring partner to aid in his training. What he gets is the battle of his life! Meanwhile, Yamcha and the others continue their long journey to reach Karin Tower, in hopes of receiving training from the wise Master.
items.title: Goku's Doll

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 131 Walking Their Own Ways.mkv
items.summary: Preparing for the Tenkaichi Budokai, Goku gets some important training tips from Mr. Popo. Meanwhile, Tenshinhan, Yamcha, Chiaotzu and Kuririn make their way to Karin Tower for some training of their own. Unfortunately they are sidetracked by a village celebrating a mysterious festival to their mountain spirit. Once the mountain erupts it is up to our heroes to put a lid on the active volcano!
items.title: Walking Their Own Ways

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 132 Hotter than Lava.mkv
items.summary: While Goku continues his training, Tenshinhan, Yamcha, Chiaotzu and Kuririn find themselves in a very hot situation! A remote village is threatened by an erupting volcano and it is up to the good guys to put a lid on it. The time has come to put their new training to the test!
items.title: Hotter than Lava

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 133 Changes.mkv
items.summary: Warriors the world over are lining up to compete as the Tenkaichi Budokai prepares to get under way. Unfortunately, all of the Turtle Hermit's pupils are missing, including Goku. With the entry-deadline approaching, the competitive future of our heroes look bleak, as does Muten Roshi's patience.
items.title: Changes

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 134 Preliminary Peril.mkv
items.summary: The Tenkaichi Budokai gets underway as Goku and the others compete in the exciting preliminary round. But the competition threatens to turn ugly when Goku gets a visit from an old adversary.
items.title: Preliminary Peril

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 135 Battle of the Eight.mkv
items.summary: The preliminary round continues as Goku, Yamcha, Kuririn, and Tenshinhan battle one opponent after another in hopes of advancing to the semi-final round. Meanwhile, the Turtle Hermit is confronted by an old rival.
items.title: Battle of the Eight

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 136 Tien Shinhan vs. Mercenary Tao.mkv
items.summary: The Budokai gets underway as Tenshinhan battles his former mentor turned cyborg, Tao Pai Pai. Tensions run high as the former assassin attempts to take Tenshinhan down - permanently!
items.title: Tien Shinhan vs. Mercenary Tao

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 137 Anonymous Proposal.mkv
items.summary: Goku takes on his most lovely opponent yet in the second match of the Tenkaichi Budokai. Know only as Anonymous, the beautiful warrior's identity is a mysterious as her fierce anger toward Goku, who must win the match in order to learn her real name.
items.title: Anonymous Proposal

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 138 The Mysterious Hero.mkv
items.summary: The Budokai continues with a double header! First up, Kuririn battles Ma Junior, Piccolo Daimao's alter ego, and every bit as powerful. Yamcha jumps in the ring next, opposing Shen, whose meek appearance may hide a darker threat.
items.title: The Mysterious Hero

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 139 Rematch.mkv
items.summary: Yamcha scratches to stay in the ring as Shen reveals his true ability - and identity. Goku and Tenshinhan must fight one another in a friendly rematch to claim the last remaining spot for the semi-finals.
items.title: Rematch

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 140 Goku Gains Speed.mkv
items.summary: As the battle between Tenshinhan and Goku rages, Goku unloads a heavy burden, one that may shift the balance in the extraordinary showdown. All eyes turn to Tenshinhan as an embarrassing moment spurs him to make a dangerous choice.
items.title: Goku Gains Speed

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 141 The Four Faces of Tien.mkv
items.summary: Goku has always been able to handle himself in the ring, but when his fight with Tenshinhan turns into a war against an army, he finds himself in serious jeopardy. Tenshinhan's new technique may spell the end for our hero!
items.title: The Four Faces of Tien

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 142 Kami vs. Piccolo.mkv
items.summary: Goku is eager to fight Ma Junior, but God fears his inexperience will be his downfall. Shen takes on Ma Junior in the last round of the semi-finals, where his shocking agenda is revealed.
items.title: Kami vs. Piccolo

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 143 Battle for the Future.mkv
items.summary: Goku faces the ultimate test as he confronts his greatest nemesis in the final round of the Budokai. This time his fight is for more than the title. The future of the free world is at stake!
items.title: Battle for the Future

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 144 Super Kamehameha.mkv
items.summary: The battle to save the planet continues as Goku tries to take down Ma Junior in the final match of the 23rd Tenkaichi Budokai. Goku has an ultimate weapon: The Ultimate Super Kamehameha Wave. However, if he uses it to destroy Ma Junior, God will be sacrificed, having been trapped inside Ma Junior's stomach.
items.title: Super Kamehameha

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 145 Junior No More.mkv
items.summary: Ma Junior reveals a startling secret that shocks the tournament. Goku finds himself facing a huge dilemma, as he fights for the championship becomes the fight for survival!
items.title: Junior No More

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 146 Goku's Trap.mkv
items.summary: As the exhausting battle between Goku and Ma Junior continues, Goku avoids disaster by taking the battle within. Ma Junior surprises all when he unveils a new threat!
items.title: Goku's Trap

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 147 Goku Hangs On.mkv
items.summary: The Tenkaichi Budokai begins to fall to piece as Ma Junior unveils a technique that not only threatens to destroy Goku, but his friends as well. Even the mighty God believes that there is no way for Goku to survive in this winner-take-all massacre!
items.title: Goku Hangs On

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 148 The Victor.mkv
items.summary: The end of the 23rd Tenkaichi Budokai finds Goku struggling for survival as Ma Junior gets the upper hand, poised to take the Title and his life. God devises a way to rescue the young hero, but his plan calls for the ultimate sacrifice!
items.title: The Victor

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 149 Dress in Flames.mkv
items.summary: Eager to announce their wedding plans, Goku and Chichi return to her father's kingdom. The good news is short-lived when the Gyumao's castle goes up in flames! Goku embarks on a quest to find a sacred tool, which can save the Gyumao and his future with Chichi.
items.title: Dress in Flames

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 150 The Fire-Eater.mkv
items.summary: Goku and Chichi's search for the Basho-sen leads them into the heart of a fiery volcano. Once inside, they must face a mighty creature that consumes flames: the Fire-Eater!
items.title: The Fire-Eater

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 151 Outrageous Octagon.mkv
items.summary: Goku's search for the Basho-sen leads him to a treacherous mountain that has a strange curse. Chichi is faced with the biggest mess of her life when she meets a mysterious old woman, while the Gyumao tries to flee the raging fires that threaten to destroy his castle!
items.title: Outrageous Octagon

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 152 Mystery of the Dark World.mkv
items.summary: After the Basho-sen fails to put out the fire threatening the Gyumao, Goku and Chichi set out to find the Eightfold Furnace, believed to be the last hope for extinguishing the deadly blaze. But before they can complete their quest, Goku must solve the mystery of the next world.
items.title: Mystery of the Dark World

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Dragon Ball The Complete Series (1995â€“2003)/Episode 153 The End, the Beginning.mkv
items.summary: Goku and Chichi must travel to Mt. Gogyo in a last ditch effort to save her father, the Gyumao, from the deadly magical flames, which threaten to consume his kingdom. Before Goku can complete his quest, he must fan the flames of Fate and hope he does not get burned!
items.title: The End, the Beginning

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x01 - I, Duckman.mkv
items.summary: We are introduced to Duckman, who's ignored by his family and feels under appreciated, he is searching for something to be remembered by. The agency receives a package that contains a bomb that goes of in the office. Duckman is happy someone cared enough to try and kill him so he visits the sender in prison. Only that suspect also receives a package.
items.title: I, Duckman

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x02 - T.V. or Not to Be.mkv
items.summary: Duckman is watching a TV program, but the family takes over the set when Mother Mirabelle's Home Miracle Network program starts airing. The family demands that Duckman help find Mother Mirabelle's stolen painting that helps create miracles. Duckman reluctantly agrees, but he is skeptical until he experiences his own miracle.
items.title: T.V. or Not to Be

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x03 - Gripes of Wrath.mkv
items.summary: A comment Duckman makes at the unveiling of a new supercomputer, named Loretta, makes the world a better place to live in, for a while anyway.
items.title: Gripes of Wrath

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x04 - Psyche.mkv
items.summary: Feeling inadequate and hard up, Duckman gets a bill job. The detectives then get a job researching the lives of two large breasted women, but Duckman runs away from it. Seeking further help, takes him into his psyche where he confronts what has really been troubling him.
items.title: Psyche

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x05 - Gland of Opportunity.mkv
items.summary: Duckman receives the adrenal gland of a daredevil via a transplant at an amusement park clinic. The new gland gives him loads of confidence.
items.title: Gland of Opportunity

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x06 - Ride the High School.mkv
items.summary: Duckman receives a letter offering Ajax a chance to go to a boarding school for gifted children. After visiting Ajax's current school, Duckman decides that Ajax must go to the boarding school. The family begins to miss Ajax's presence. Cornfed decodes one of Ajax's letter's and they go to the school to bring Ajax back, but it turns out the school is a front for Duckman's arch-nemesis, ""King"" Chicken.
items.title: Ride the High School

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x07 - A Civil War.mkv
items.summary: Duckman is jealous when everyone showers Cornfed with their attention, so he fires him while working their next case, which involves the ""murder"" of the owner of a Steak and Waffle on a Stick factory.
items.title: A Civil War

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x08 - Not So Easy Riders.mkv
items.summary: Duckman receives a letter from the IRS. The IRS agent is tough and Duckman is given 24 hours to pay $29,587.42 in back taxes. After asking his family for help and being rejected and lectured, Duckman tries anything. When he can't raise the funds, he and Cornfed go on the run and then on the road. Bernice falls for the IRS agent who's staying at the house waiting for Duckman to call.
items.title: Not So Easy Riders

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x09 - It's the Thing of the Principal.mkv
items.summary: Bernice is worried about Ajax, who's not been eating and has been sent to the principal every day this week. Duckman and Cornfed go undercover in the school to find out what's up with Ajax. It turns out that Ajax is in love with the vice principal and she's in love with him. They take off together with plans to get married, south of the border. Duckman and Bernice pose as a couple and go after them.
items.title: It's the Thing of the Principal
items.titleSort: It's the Thing of the Principal

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x10 - Cellar Beware.mkv
items.summary: Bernice decides they're going to act together as a family. For their first activity together, she invites the neighbors over for the monthly meeting of the block association. When a home security expert shows up, his pitch gets Duckman to buy the most elaborate security system, the ""Interlopen Fuhrer 2000,"" which of course doesn't do the job and then Duckman fixes it...
items.title: Cellar Beware

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x11 - American Dicks.mkv
items.summary: The Duckman detective agency, the only agency not affected by the nationwide detective strike, becomes the focus of TV show American Dicks who are looking to solve their 100th case. Eventually, Duckman gets a case; the mission is to find the mayor.
items.title: American Dicks

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x12 - About Face.mkv
items.summary: Duckman calls 911 in an emergency and falls in love with the voice on the other end of the line. When they meet, her looks leave a whole lot to be desired. Then she gets a complete makeover that changes her life.
items.title: About Face

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 1/Duckman - 1x13 - Joking the Chicken.mkv
items.summary: A group of comedians hire Duckman to stop a pathetic mild mannered politically correct chicken whose ""clean"" stand up routine becomes a comedy sensation. The chicken's routines are funny to everyone except Duckman, who soon discovers the source of his popularity.
items.title: Joking the Chicken

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 2/Duckman - 2x01 - Papa Oom M.O.W. M.O.W..mkv
items.summary: While trying to grab a couple of women in the ass, Duckman saves the president's life. When this fact is later revealed, Duckman tries to capitalize on his sleazy image.
items.title: Papa Oom M.O.W. M.O.W.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 2/Duckman - 2x02 - Married Alive.mkv
items.summary: Bernice returns home with news that she is getting married to a self-made billionaire who plans to take her and the kids away with him to Europe, leaving Duckman alone.
items.title: Married Alive

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 2/Duckman - 2x03 - Days of Whining and Neurosis.mkv
items.summary: Duckman & Cornfed go undercover into an exclusive celebrity-filled health spa to investigate one of the support groups.
items.title: Days of Whining and Neurosis

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 2/Duckman - 2x04 - Inherit the Judgment The Dope's Trial.mkv
items.summary: Duckman, in search of his free clock radio, takes the family out to the desert. They wind up in a small town where ""King"" Chicken is the sheriff and Duckman is put on trial for being a heretic.
items.title: Inherit the Judgment: The Dope's Trial
items.titleSort: Inherit the Judgment: The Dope's Trial

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 2/Duckman - 2x05 - America the Beautiful.mkv
items.summary: As the disclaimer says at the beginning this episode is full ""of heavy handed and over-obvious allegory,"" when for some children, Duckman and Cornfed search for what has become of a beautiful model named America.
items.title: America the Beautiful

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 2/Duckman - 2x06 - The Germ Turns.mkv
items.summary: The family goes to a new age fair and at one of the booths, Duckman meets his mother who's been reincarnated as a ""highly infectious germ"". He learns that if he parents his children correctly he won't come back as germ, so he showers his kids with too much affection.
items.title: The Germ Turns

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 2/Duckman - 2x07 - In the Nam of the Father.mkv
items.summary: The son Cornfed never knew he had arrives at the office and Cornfed travels back to Vietnam to find the mother and the truth. Duckman takes his family along on the trip for a much needed vacation and must also deal with the flashbacks he is experiencing.
items.title: In the Nam of the Father
items.titleSort: In the Nam of the Father

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 2/Duckman - 2x08 - Research and Destroy.mkv
items.summary: Ajax's natural talent for poetry makes him popular. Duckman gets him signed to a contract for a job creating greeting cards, but Ajax isn't happy with his new occupation.
items.title: Research and Destroy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 2/Duckman - 2x09 - Clip Job.mkv
items.summary: Duckman is kidnapped by an irate viewer who doesn't like the lack of morals portrayed on his television show.
items.title: Clip Job

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x01 - Noir Gang.mkv
items.summary: Feeling ""creatively obligated by a film-noir parody,"" Cornfed calls their new client ""a dame,"" whose name is Tamara La Boinque. Later he confesses to a priest about betraying his partner, when they both fall in love with their client.
items.title: Noir Gang

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x02 - Forbidden Fruit.mkv
items.summary: Duckman is slapped with a sexual harassment charge by the French nanny that Bernice has hired to tutor the boys. It seems the nanny isn't who she appears to be. In search of solitude Duckman moves in with Fluffy and Uranus; even they reach their breaking point with him.
items.title: Forbidden Fruit

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x03 - Grandma-ma's Flatulent Adventure.mkv
items.summary: The family makes plans to put Grandma-ma in a rest home. While taking her there, Duckman gets distracted and loses track of her. Grandma-ma embarks on a flatulent adventure and later when Cornfed and Duckman find her, she appears to be dead. Duckman makes the funeral arrangements.
items.title: Grandma-ma's Flatulent Adventure

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x04 - Color of Naught.mkv
items.summary: Duckman again foils King Chicken's plot for revenge. This time King Chicken has produced a product that makes everything beautiful, everything except Duckman. The only problem being is that this product is actually a virus that de-evolves everything. Duckman must again battle King Chicken and save the world.
items.title: Color of Naught

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x05 - Sperms of Endearment.mkv
items.summary: Bernice, Duckmans sister-in-law, decides she wants to have a child of her own. After trying the dating scene she decides to give artificial insemination a go.  Due to a mis-communication and over abundance of, er, 'product', the service gives her Duckmans 'donation'. Hilarity ensues as Duckman and Bernice are incompatible in every [in] conceivable way.
items.title: Sperms of Endearment

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x06 - A Room With a Bellevue.mkv
items.summary:
Duckman gets placed in a mental institution after pleading temporary insanity to a charge of public ranting. He likes the strict regimentation of the institution (compared to the anarchy and choas of outside the institution) so much that he decides to have himself permanently commited. Cornfed comes to rescue Duckman from the institution, but is to late as he has already been given shock treatment. Luckily Cornfed has a book on brain surgery and gets Duckman back to 'normal'.

[note: the original version of this episode has a  small section where Duckman is being dragged through a room where some residents are being given a test, and Dr. Stein asks them about seeing Duckman and a question of time. For some strange reason this scene is usually cut.]
items.title: A Room With a Bellevue

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x07 - Apocalypse Not.mkv
items.summary: After the city gets attacked by one of Duckmans over-inflated dolls, the city decides to have an emergency drill where all the residents go underground till the drill passes. Duckman fails to know about the drill and has a city-wide 'party' (involving mass destrution) while all the residents are gone. Eventually the residents return to chase Duckman out of town.
items.title: Apocalypse Not

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x08 - Clear and Presidente Danger.mkv
items.summary: Duckman and group win a trip to a third-world country. Duckman starts a revolution with his ranting and gets placed into power where he becomes as corrupt as the last rulling paty. This requires Cornfed to form a revolution and rescue Duckman and group.
items.title: Clear and Presidente Danger

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x09 - The Girls of Route Canal.mkv
items.summary: Charles and Mambo are in love and look to Duckman for advice. He tells them a Bridges of Madison County-esque story of how he and their mother met and fell in love.
items.title: The Girls of Route Canal

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x10 - The Mallardian Candidate.mkv
items.summary: Former comedian Iggy Catalpa hires Duckman to investigate a conspiracy where the only evidence is a sock missing from his laundry. The conspirators capture Duckman and brainwash him into killing the only one who can stop them, Cornfed.
items.title: The Mallardian Candidate

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x11 - Pig Amok.mkv
items.summary: (Willabald Feivel) Cornfed finds out from his father via a documentary co-written with Ken Burns, that he has a genetic disease that gives him a choice, either lose his virginity, or die in 24 hours. Duckman tries to help him out, but Bernice saves the day and Cornfed pledges his undying love. He becomes dejected when she rejects him and tries to commit suicide.
items.title: Pig Amok

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x12 - The Once and Future Duck.mkv
items.summary: Ajax opens a rift in the time/space continuum with his clock radio. Duckman discovers from a future version of himself that his future hinges on Charles and Mambo's tuba recital. Unfortunately Duckman tries to use these visits from his future selves to make a his decisions and suddenly discover every little decision he makes has a big impact on his future.
items.title: The Once and Future Duck

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x13 - The One With Lisa Kudrow in a Small Role (a.k.a. Planet of the Dopes).mkv
items.summary: Ajax is abducted by redneck aliens and taken to a planet where Duckman is praised as a deity and Ajax revered as ""The son of Dod.""
items.title: The One With Lisa Kudrow in a Small Role (a.k.a. Planet of the Dopes)
items.titleSort: One With Lisa Kudrow in a Small Role (a.k.a. Planet of the Dopes)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x14 - Aged Heat.mkv
items.summary: A Grandma-ma look-a-like robber switches places with the her to make an escape. Duckman suspects that Grandma-ma isn't quite herself, of course no one believes him. The Agnes reveals herself and holds the family hostage.
items.title: Aged Heat

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x15 - They Craved Duckman's Brain!.mkv
items.summary: Duckman is cast in a hospital educational film with Joe Walsh; for his part he is put into a MRI chamber. The film crew is thrown out of the lab and Duckman forgotten. Left too long in the chamber, a mutation occurs which a doctor identifies as a cure for cancer. Now everyone wants Duckman's brain for their own purposes. Meanwhile, Agnes is still impersonating Grandma-ma.
items.title: They Craved Duckman's Brain!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x16 - The Road to Dendron.mkv
items.summary: A parody of the Hope/Crosby Road pictures is done in this episode as Duckman and Cornfed act as chaperones for Ajax's class trip to the Sudan. Ajax is kidnapped. Duckman and Cornfed must rescue Ajax from a Sultan, his Fakir and a beautiful princess.
items.title: The Road to Dendron

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x17 - Exile in Guyville.mkv
items.summary: A young child is related the tale of how Duckman and Bernice led a nationwide division of sexes, all this because of his ad for lingerie. Duckman and the men move to the west coast. Bernice and the woman move to the east coast. The children have a different idea.
items.title: Exile in Guyville

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x18 - The Longest Weekend.mkv
items.summary: Duckman and the neighbors get together to form an association after another neighborhood association appears to be getting preferential treatment from the city. Duckman is elected head of the association and he becomes Patton-like as the two neighborhood associations go to war. The civil war breaks out within their neighborhood association.
items.title: The Longest Weekend

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x19 - The Amazing Colossal Duckman.mkv
items.summary: Through a unique combination of chemicals, Duckman gets a rare blood disease that causes him to grow several inches each time he gets angry and rants & raves. Realizing that he can't control himself after growing several feet, Duckman exiles himself to a desert island.
items.title: The Amazing Colossal Duckman

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 3/Duckman - 3x20 - Cock Tales for Four.mkv
items.summary: Duckman and Bernice go to meet the parent's of Ajax's girlfriend. The parents turn out to be ""King"" Chicken and his wife; surprisingly for the moment he and Duckman make up. Bernice and the ""King"" also mend their fence; however, Honey makes a play for Duckman to put things back to normal.
items.title: Cock Tales for Four

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x01 - Dammit, Hollywood.mkv
items.summary: Annoyed with the current state of the film industry, Duckman goes to Hollywood to demand his $7 back. Instead, he falls into the plot of a soon-to-be deposed studio executive, a man who's looking for a patsy to run the studio into the ground in hopes of saving his own job. Duckman becomes head of Paradox Pictures, where ""if it's a good movie its a Paradox"". He quickly begins running through the studio's money, signs a secretary to a 340 million dollar deal to star in a movie in her underpants. The deposed executive also arranges it so that Duckman manages to alienate the studio's three biggest action stars.
items.title: Dammit, Hollywood

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x02 - Coolio Runnings.mkv
items.summary: With the Father & Son Games coming up, Duckman looks for an alternative to competing with Ajax. He spots a more than adequate replacement in recording artist Coolio, who's returned to school to replace his high school diploma. Coolio does not compete with Duckman. Ajax competes with Duckman and even tho they don't win, it has made Duckman and Ajax's bond stronger.
items.title: Coolio Runnings

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x03 - Aged Heat 2 Women in Heat.mkv
items.summary: Duckman is imprisoned for killing Fluffy and Uranus, again. However, he is accidentally sent to a women's prison. A dream of his comes true! In fact Duckman fits in quite well and becomes the star attraction in the warden's side business, a dance ring. Everything's going great until Suzy comes along.
items.title: Aged Heat 2: Women in Heat

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x04 - All About Elliott.mkv
items.summary: Duckman and Cornfed hire a college intern for the agency. The intern undermines Cornfed's reputation and indulges Duckman's self-destructive behavior. Duckman must choose between his flashy new assistant (who may be trying to kill him) and his old partner.
items.title: All About Elliott

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x05 - From Brad to Worse.mkv
items.summary: Duckman finds an old high school classmate who's been homeless due to something Duckman did to him 20 years ago. Duckman's attempts to help only make things worse.
items.title: From Brad to Worse

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x06 - Bonfire of the Panties.mkv
items.summary: Cornfed along with Charles and Mambo prepare the ultimate aphrodisiac for Duckman to turn his love life around. They give him a limited amount of the potion, but he quickly replicates it in huge batches. Now he has more woman than he can deal with. Bernice discovers what is going on and demands that he stop. When the real thing occurs between Duckman and actress Courtney Thorne-Smith, no one believes him.
items.title: Bonfire of the Panties

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x07 - Role With It.mkv
items.summary: Duckman takes the family and the staff on a holiday to a real Indian reservation, with a casino. While there, a psychiatrist notices Duckman and the rest of the family's overall self-destructive behavior. She offers them treatment that involves a role-playing session that uncovers some of their real issues.
items.title: Role With It

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x08 - Ajax and Ajaxer.mkv
items.summary: Duckman and Cornfed are hired to perform surveillance on a laboratory that is performing experiments on intelligence formulas. Cornfed accidentally swallows a ""Get Dumb"" formula, that falls in with the plans of the scientist who created it. If Cornfed gets cured, will Ajax lose his first true friend?
items.title: Ajax and Ajaxer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x09 - With Friends Like These.mkv
items.summary: Duckman quests for friendship when Cornfed is the only guest at his surprise party. He begins hanging out at a coffee shop that is filled with a group of twenty-somethings named Ditzi, Bobby, Sassy, Pete and Marion. Together they discuss their ""problems"" a la Friends with a side of Ellen.
items.title: With Friends Like These

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x10 - A Trophied Duck.mkv
items.summary: Duckman and the gang travel to San Francisco to attend Dickcon 97. He thinks he is being honored with an ""achievement"" award. When he gets there, he encounters an old rival from detective school. The rival is running the event and takes every opportunity to humiliate him. One of these methods involves an attempt to find a kidnapped Cornfed.
items.title: A Trophied Duck

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x11 - A Star is Abhorred.mkv
items.summary: Duckman takes the family and Cornfed out for dinner. The karaoke machine comes out and Bernice's rantings against Duckman are heard by a record company big-wig. He markets her as an Alanis Morrisette type of singing sensation; however, the tour takes a toll on her and the family.
items.title: A Star is Abhorred

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x12 - Bev Takes a Holiday.mkv
items.summary: Bernice travels to Washington to assume her new role as Congresswoman. Duckman spots a woman who happens to look like Beatrice, but gets hit by a bus. It turns out that she is Beatrice and Bernice's long lost triplet. Bev realizes the only way to keep Duckman alive is to pretend to be Beatrice.
items.title: Bev Takes a Holiday

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x13 - Love! Anger! Kvetching! (a.k.a. Ain't Gonna Be No Mo No Mo').mkv
items.summary: Duckman plans a big poker for the evening. Unfortunately before the game his obnoxious Uncle Mo arrives and claims he is dying. To avoid the curse that befell his cousin, Duckman tries to wait on him hand and foot. Just how much of his Uncle can he take?
items.title: Love! Anger! Kvetching! (a.k.a. Ain't Gonna Be No Mo No Mo')
items.titleSort: Love! Anger! Kvetching! (a.k.a. Ain't Gonna Be No Mo No Mo')

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x14 - Duckman and Cornfed in 'Haunted Society Plumbers'.mkv
items.summary: Duckman and Cornfed become plumbers and their first job takes them to a society gathering in a mansion. While not doing his job, Duckman discovers that the cursed ""Sharon Stone"" is missing; he and Cornfed try to recover the diamond before the hostess discovers the theft. After the diamond is revealed to be missing, its curse comes into play and traps them in the mansion.
items.title: Duckman and Cornfed in 'Haunted Society Plumbers'
items.titleSort: Duckman and Cornfed in 'Haunted Society Plumbers'

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x15 - Ebony, Baby.mkv
items.summary: Cornfed leaves for a much-needed vacation. While he is away, Duckman becomes mesmerized by a black model/private eye who quickly gets him involved in a world of murder, power, lust and every black exploitation clichÃƒÂ© that exists with a side of a Spelling/Goldberg production.
items.title: Ebony, Baby

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x16 - Vuuck, as in Duck.mkv
items.summary: Duckman inherits a minor league baseball team as the dying wish of the owner who is trying to keep the team from hands of a banker. To boost attendance he stages a series of stunts, that humiliate and scare the players into quitting. He ""hires"" nine super-models to take their place and they are an instant success. Cornfed teaches them the fundamentals of baseball and they become a great team. The banker institutes a scheme to prevent the supermodels from winning the big game and Cornfed discovers his other scheme on the Internet in the newsgroup alt.villians.greedy-schemes.
items.title: Vuuck, as in Duck

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x17 - Crime, Punishment, War, Peace, and the Idiot.mkv
items.summary: Beverly asks Bernice if she knows anything about Grandma-ma's past. The coma-bound Grandma-ma recalls her past in a series of flashbacks that involves a tortured romance with two characters who look and sound a lot like Cornfed (Petrov) and Duckman (Trigorin) with Russian accents.
items.title: Crime, Punishment, War, Peace, and the Idiot
items.titleSort: Crime, Punishment, War, Peace, and the Idiot

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x18 - Kidney, Popsicle, and Nuts.mkv
items.summary: Duckman needs a new kidney. To get one requires a donation from a blood relative. He searches for his father, who he thought was cryogenically frozen. Instead he discovers that the man he thought was his father, wasn't. Using the power of the Microsoft Network (Blatant Plug!), the twins and Cornfed find where dad is currently living. Duckman and Cornfed travel there, only to find that his is a paranoid schizophrenic who's formed his own country.
items.title: Kidney, Popsicle, and Nuts

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x19 - The Tami Show.mkv
items.summary: Duckman backs his car into a cute girl in front the house. Finding out that she is on her own, Beverly and the family invite her to stay; however, Beverly becomes the victim when Tami tries to takeover a have a ""perfect family.""
items.title: The Tami Show

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x20 - My Feral Lady.mkv
items.summary: Duckman purchases a mail-order bride, from Tetzloff; however, she's really a jungle savage. With Cornfed's help, they attempt to civilize her a'la My Fair Lady. He asks for her hand in marriage on a ""Surprise Proposals"" episode of Leeza and things go awry when the flashbulbs go off.
items.title: My Feral Lady

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x21 - Westward, No!.mkv
items.summary: Cornfed invites Beverly to join him on a trip to his Aunt's catfish ranch. Duckman, jealous of Cornfed's interest in Bev, tags along for the ride. After getting the ranch hands fired, Duckman and the gang must help the foreman, Big Jack McBastard, on the big catfish drive to Texas. On part of their drive involves crossing ""Hell's Toilet,"" where ""the days are so hot they can boil your brain and the nights are colder than David Caruso's film career."" After Duckman accidentally kills Big Jack, they are on their own.
items.title: Westward, No!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x22 - Short, Plush and Deadly.mkv
items.summary: The family goes on a dream holiday camping trip. At the park, they run into Fluffy and Uranus who are also on holiday. However, Duckman quickly puts them to work and gets himself banished from the campground. He takes Fluffy, Uranus and Cornfed with him off into the woods, but bees sting the accompanying trio. Cornfed's head swells and an allergic reaction causes Fluffy and Uranus to grow to gigantic proportions and become homicidal. Hearing Duckman's screams, Beverly and a reluctant Bernice go to the rescue leaving entertainer Jim Bailey keeps the boys and Grandma-ma entertained.
items.title: Short, Plush and Deadly

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x23 - How to Suck in Business Without Really Trying.mkv
items.summary: Duckman sells his identity to the Variecom corporation for $1000, which he immediately spends. Unable to use his own name or image, he is left penniless. He even tries to become a Duckman impersonator, until he is ""downsized."" Then he conceives a plan to get his self-respect and identity back. Meanwhile, Cornfed leaves to rejoin the 80's band A Flock of Seagulls.
items.title: How to Suck in Business Without Really Trying
items.titleSort: How to Suck in Business Without Really Trying

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x24 - You've Come a Wrong Way, Baby.mkv
items.summary: Mambo is caught with a cigarette in his mouth; Bernice takes action in Congress. A tobacco company CEO invites her and the family to enjoy the hospitality of the tobacco industry. When Bernice won't change her position, they are put to work picking tobacco. Rescue seems hopeless, until Agnes Delrooney, reveals that she has been hiding out as Grandma-ma all this time. She makes an escape, with Duckman handcuffed to her.
items.title: You've Come a Wrong Way, Baby
items.titleSort: You've Come a Wrong Way, Baby

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x25 - Hamlet 2 This Time It's Personal.mkv
items.summary: Cornfed undergoes analysis and relates this tale about Duckman seeing the ghost of his uncle who says that Duckman's father was murdered by King Chicken. Duckman hangs with Bernice and King Chicken while pretending to be crazy. Cornfed realizes that Duckman is living out the plot of ""Hamlet,"" that will eventually lead to Duckman's death.
items.title: Hamlet 2: This Time It's Personal

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x26 - Das Sub (a.k.a. Class Warfare).mkv
items.summary: Convicted of fraud, Duckman is sentenced to 5,000 hours of community service. He is sent to a dangerous inner-city high school, located a half a block from his house, where he becomes a substitute teacher and it turns out that his is the most ""Dangerous Mind.""
items.title: Das Sub (a.k.a. Class Warfare)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x27 - Where No Duckman Has Gone Before.mkv
items.summary: In a send-up of the Paramount franchise, Eric Tiberius Duckman, captain of the starship Enterprise matches wits against the evil Khan Chicken.
items.title: Where No Duckman Has Gone Before
items.titleSort: Where No Duckman Has Gone Before

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Duckman/Season 4/Duckman - 4x28 - Four Weddings Inconceivable.mkv
items.summary: At the wedding of Dr. Ben Stein, a series of emotional epiphanies lead to an amazing set of marriage proposals. King Chicken proposes to Bernice. Cornfed proposes to Beverly. Duckman proposes to his new love, King Chicken's ex Honey. After many arguments between the principles, Duckman says he will make all the arrangements, thereby letting everyone blame him. Despite his arrangements, the ceremony goes off with the appropriate hitches, except that Duckman finds out something that Cornfed forgot to tell him.
items.title: Four Weddings Inconceivable

items.summary: In this murder mystery special, The Griffins as well as all the other major characters become trapped in a mansion while they are killed off one by one.
items.title: And Then There Were Fewer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E02.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: When Brian learns that Rush Limbaugh is going to be at the Quahog Mall for a book-signing, he decides to go down there and give him a piece of his left-wing mind. But when Rush unexpectedly comes to Brian's rescue, Brian has a political change of heart
items.title: Excellence in Broadcasting

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E03.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: After Peter catches Carter having an affair, he is forced into keeping a secret. But when Peter accidentally spills the beans, Lois' mom demands a divorce, and Peter is in charge of Carter's return to bachelorhood.
items.title: Welcome Back Carter

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E04.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary:
Peter and Joe team up to execute a series of painful and humiliating Halloween pranks on unsuspecting family, friends and neighbors.

While Brian shows Stewie the ropes of trick-or-treating, Meg sets out to attend her first high school Halloween party with high hopes for the evening.
items.title: Halloween on Spooner Street

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E05.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: When Peter receives tickets to a boxing match as a birthday gift, he volunteers Lois to compete. To everyone's surprise, Lois dominates in the ring, and Peter decides to become her fight promoter. Her frustration with Peter turns into motivation in the ring as the housewife turns champion.
items.title: Baby, You Knock Me Out

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E06.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Feeling discouraged with the progress of his writing career, Brian decides to throw in the towel until Stewie become his manager and one of his books hits the bestseller list. But when the fame goes to his head, Brian gets a wake-up call from Bill Maher.
items.title: Brian Writes a Bestseller

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E07.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Stewieâ€™s favorite thing after his teddy bear, Rupert, is Christmas. So when he hears that Santa is making an appearance at the mall, he begs Brian to take him so that he can tell Santa in person what he wants for Christmas. Brian begrudgingly takes Stewie to the mall, only to get the brush-off from Santa. As a result, Stewie and Brian travel to the North Pole to find Santa and teach him a lesson in holiday cheer.
items.title: Road to the North Pole

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E08.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Peter needs a new kidney after his energy-drink addiction causes renal failure. Meanwhile, Chris is chosen to introduce United States President Barack Obama at his school after winning an essay contest. Trouble is, Meg wrote the essay.
items.title: New Kidney in Town

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E09.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Lois becomes friends with Joyce Kinney, the new local news anchor, and Joyce convinces Lois to let her do a story on her as the model American housewife. The television story makes Lois look terrible, and Joyce is unapologetic, leaving Lois no choice but to right a wrong.
items.title: And I'm Joyce Kinney

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E10.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Brian and Peter are required to attend a 12-step program to deal with their drinking problems; Death gives Peter a glimpse of what life would be like without alcohol.
items.title: Friends of Peter G.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E11.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: On the search to find a new hobby, Chris meets a puppeteer named Franz, an old friend of Herbert's. Despite Herbert's warnings, Chris and Franz remain friends until Franz's checkered past is suddenly revealed.
items.title: German Guy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E12.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: When Bonnie goes out of town, Meg offers to check in on Joe, but she soon becomes a little too involved and starts freaking everyone out - especially Joe. Meanwhile, Stewie thinks he's losing his edge as the toughest baby on the block, so he hooks himself up to a machine that is supposed to make him more evil than ever before.
items.title: The Hand That Rocks the Wheelchair

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E13.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Chris and Meg think their parents have it easy, and Peter and Lois beg to differ, so in order to teach them a lesson, they all trade roles. Chris goes to work at the brewery while Meg runs the house. While things start off well, it's not long until the stress of running a household and being the sole breadwinner break down Chris and Meg.
items.title: Trading Places

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E14.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: When the local dry cleaner loses Peterâ€™s favorite white shirt, he goes ballistic. Meanwhile, Brian tries to score on a date with a new friend, Denise, but ends up striking out. Instead of calling it quits on love, he decides to enlist Quagmireâ€™s help, but things get nasty when they start to compete for the affections of each otherâ€™s old flames, Cheryl Tiegs and Jillian Russell.
items.title: Tiegs for Two

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E15.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: When Mayor West marries Loisâ€™ sister, Carol, they move into the Griffinâ€™s house to be one big â€œhappyâ€ family. To make room for everyone, Stewie is bumped out of his room and takes over Chrisâ€™ room, but not everyone is annoyed by the change. Peter and Mayor West bond and become best friends.
items.title: Brothers & Sisters

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E16.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Stewie and Brian go back in time to stop Bertram from killing Leonardo da Vinci in order to erase Stewie from the universe.
items.title: The Big Bang Theory

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S09/Family.Guy.S09E17.720p.WEB-DL.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Lois goes to Paris with Bonnie, but she soon reveals to Lois that she plans on having an affair. Lois must find a way to save Bonnie and Joe's marriage. Meanwhile, Peter decides to homeschool Meg and Chris during a so-called goat flu pandemic, but there is mixed results with Peter homeschooling his children.
items.title: Foreign Affairs

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S10/Family.Guy.S10E01.720p.HDTV.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Peter blows his savings on lottery tickets and the family writes it off as one of his usual shenanigans until they end up millionaires. In true Griffin fashion, they canâ€™t handle the good fortune and struggle to stay grounded.
items.title: Lottery Fever

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S10/Family.Guy.S10E02.720p.HDTV.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary:
While the Griffins are housebound during a hurricane, Brian ingests psychedelic mushrooms. He sees bizarre and unsettling things, and acts accordingly. Meanwhile, the rest of the family is bored and irritable, and Meg finally lashes out at Chris, Lois and Peter for all the crap they've given her.

The crossover starts on The Cleveland Show S03E02 The Hurricane (I). It continues on American Dad! S08E02 Hurricane! (III).
items.title: Seahorse Seashell Party (II)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S10/Family.Guy.S10E03.720p.HDTV.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Quagmire lands in the hospital and his sister, Brenda, and her boyfriend, Jeff, rush to Quahog to nurse him back to health. As Glenn recovers he quickly realizes that Brenda is the one who needs help.
items.title: Screams of Silence: The Story of Brenda Q
items.titleSort: Screams of Silence: The Story of Brenda Q

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S10/Family.Guy.S10E04.720p.HDTV.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Ryan Reynolds pays a visit to Quahog and becomes obsessed with Peter Griffin. Meanwhile, Stewie tries to be a big boy and steals the family car for a joy ride but lands in a bit of trouble.
items.title: Stewie Goes for a Drive

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S10/Family.Guy.S10E05.720p.HDTV.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: When Brian finds a tennis ball from 1999, he and Stewie go back to the events of Death Has a Shadow (1999) and when they get back to present day, America goes to civil war after Brian's past self prevents 9/11. When they go back to 1999 and stop Brian from telling him about it, Brian tells his past self about Harry Potter. And they go back to the past yet again.
items.title: Back to the Pilot

items.summary: On the return from an adventurous day at an amusement park, the Griffinsâ€™ car breaks down in Amish country and they are stranded with no way out. When Meg falls for an Amish boy, the Griffins then find themselves in a crusade against the conservative locals.
items.title: Amish Guy

items.summary: Peter and the guys take a stand against their wives and flee to the Deep South on a road trip. On their Deep South road trip, Peter and the guys earn a one-way ticket to jail, then decide to make a run for it.
items.title: Cool Hand Peter

items.title: Grumpy Old Man

items.summary: When Meg finally turns 18, Quagmire seizes the opportunity to pursue his next romantic conquest. As the new couple's relationship blossoms, Peter stops at nothing to come in between his innocent - well, somewhat innocent - daughter and his creepy friend.
items.title: Meg and Quagmire

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Family Guy/S10/Family.Guy.S10E11.720p.HDTV.ReEnc-Max.mkv
items.summary: Brian starts dating a blind girl and things get a little dicey when she divulges that she hates dogs. So in the end, Lois decides to get the old one back.

Meanwhile, Peter has a religious experience of his own.
