items.title: Marge and Homer Turn a Couple Play
items.titleSort: Marge and Homer Turn a Couple Play

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E01. The Mook The Chef The Wife And Her Homer.mp4
items.summary: Lisa's friendship with Fat Tony's son Michael prompts mob boss Tony to invite the Simpsons over for dinner. Michael says he'd rather be a chef than take over the family business, but that's before Tony is shot by a rival mobster.
items.title: The Mook, the Chef, the Wife and Her Homer
items.titleSort: Mook, the Chef, the Wife and Her Homer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E02. Jazzy And The Pussycats.mp4
items.summary: A child psychiatrist suggests drumming to channel Bart's energy, and the boy proves he's got the beat when he shows some talent on the skins.
items.title: Jazzy and the Pussycats

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E03. Please Homer Don't Hammer Em.mp4
items.summary: Marge reads Homer's carpentry books and becomes very handy at fixing things. Gender bias keeps the townspeople from accepting a female carpenter, so Marge pretends that Homer does the work. Meanwhile, Bart torments Skinner when he learns the principal has an extreme allergy to peanuts.
items.title: Please Homer, Don't Hammer 'Em

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E04. Treehouse Of Horror Xvii.mp4
items.summary: The 17th annual Halloween trilogy. Included: "Married to the Blob," in which a meteor turns Homer into a monster; "You Gotta Know When to Golem," about a monster from Jewish folklore; and "The Day the Earth Looked Stupid," about an alien invasion.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror XVII

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E05. G.i Annoyed Grunt 2006.mp4
items.summary: Homer is bamboozled by Army recruiters and winds up in basic training, where he runs afoul of a tough-minded colonel and is assigned to play the enemy in war games.
items.title: G.I. (Annoyed Grunt)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E06. Moe N A Lisa.mp4
items.summary: Lisa sees poetry in the notes Moe sticks to the walls of his hotel room, so she sends his work to a poetry journal, which publishes it, making Moe the toast of the literary circuit.
items.title: Moe'N'a Lisa

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E07. Ice Cream Of Margie.mp4
items.summary: Homer is fired and decides to buy an ice-cream truck. Marge makes use of the mountains of Popsicle sticks from Homer's ice-cream consumption by creating sculptures of Springfield citizens with them, leading to a feature about her on the news.
items.title: Ice Cream of Margie (With the Light Blue Hair)
items.titleSort: Ice Cream of Margie (With the Light Blue Hair)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E08. The Haw-hawed Couple.mp4
items.summary: When Bart ends up the only guest at Nelson's birthday party, the bully decides he's his best friend and goes about protecting Bart in a parody of "Goodfellas." Meanwhile, Homer reads Lisa to sleep and debates on whether to reveal the book's sad ending to her.
items.title: The Haw-Hawed Couple

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E09. Kill Gil Vols 1&2.mp4
items.summary: Homer jumps into a brawl during a holiday ice-skating show. To escape the melee, Marge takes the family Christmas shopping, where a chance encounter with Gil leads to bad luck for Gil and the Simpson clan.
items.title: Kill Gil, Volumes I & II

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E10. The Wife Aquatic.mp4
items.summary: Selma and Patti's home movies make Marge nostalgic for the Barnacle Bay vacations of her youth, so Homer takes the family there, but the area has changed since the Bouviers were little girls.
items.title: The Wife Aquatic

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E11. Revenge Is A Dish Best Served Three Times.mp4
items.summary: While Homer tries to get revenge on a driver who cut him off, his family warns him of the folly of revenge by telling stories based on "The Count of Monte Cristo," "Revenge of the Nerds," and "Batman."
items.title: Revenge Is a Dish Best Served Three Times
items.titleSort: Revenge Is a Dish Best Served Three Times

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E12. Little Big Girl.mp4
items.summary: Lisa pretends to be Native American for multicultural day at school. Meanwhile, Bart finds love with an older woman.
items.title: Little Big Girl

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E13. Springfield Up.mp4
items.summary: Documentary filmer Declan Desmond returns to Springfield to finish his movie (shot in 8 year intervals) about the past of people growing up in Springfield. Homer tries to hide his apparent lack of achievements but is eventually corrected by some faith inspiring anecdotes from the other Springfieldians.
items.title: Springfield Up

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E14. Yokel Chords.mp4
items.summary: Bart has to see a psychiatrist after he starts a panic at school by telling a story about a murderous cafeteria worker. Meanwhile, Lisa tries to civilize Cletus Spuckler's hillbilly children, with mixed results.
items.title: Yokel Chords

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E15. Rome-old And Juli-eh.mp4
items.summary: Baby-sitting together Grampa and Selma seem to have lots in common and start dating,despite efforts by Patty and Homer to wreck the courtship. Eventually they marry but Abe's unfamiliarity with modern kitchen gadgets literally destroys their love nest. Meanwhile Bart and Lisa build a fort out of cardboard boxes and,in an epic battle,withstand the efforts of the box company to get their property back.
items.title: Rome-Old and Juli-Eh

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E16. Homerazzi.mp4
items.summary: After a celebrity scandal is accidentally captured in a family photo, Homer decides to become a paparazzo.
items.title: Homerazzi

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E17. Marge Gamer.mp4
items.summary: Marge goes online for the first time and becomes obsessed with a role-playing game that Bart and many of their neighbors are playing. Meanwhile, Lisa develops her own obsession--for soccer--and Homer becomes a referee.
items.title: Marge Gamer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E18. The Boys Of Bummer.mp4
items.summary: Bart goes from hero to goat on his Little League team after an error in the championship game. Meanwhile, Homer falls asleep on a bed in a department store. When he's awakened, he raves about the mattress and is given a job as a salesman.
items.title: The Boys of Bummer

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E19. Crook And Ladder.mp4
items.summary: Homer, Apu, Moe and Skinner volunteer as firemen after Homer's sleepwalking accident injures the town's firefighters. They do some light looting at the fires to make up for not being compensated, but Marge and Lisa shame them into mending their ways.
items.title: Crook and Ladder

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E20. Stop Or My Dog Will Shoot.mp4
items.summary: Homer unwittingly drags the family into a cornfield maze after attempting to leave a boring Harvest fest that Marge brought them to. When everyone except Homer escapes, Santa's Little Helper rescues him and becomes the town hero. So the Simpsons enroll him in Police Dog Academy where he's teamed with Lou.
items.title: Stop or My Dog Will Shoot!
items.titleSort: Stop or My Dog Will Shoot!

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E21. 24 Minutes.mp4
items.summary: "The Simpsons" reaches yet another milestone in the series long running history,with this,their 400th broadcast episode. The show is a send up of another hit FOX series "24",with special guest voice Keifer Sutherland playing his character from that series. This show is also the finale for season 18.
items.title: 24 Minutes

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 18/S18E22. You Kent Always Say What You Want.mp4
items.summary: Newsman Kent Brockman is fired for swearing on the air when Homer dumps coffee in his lap, but Lisa gets Brockman back in the game with her Webcam.
items.title: You Kent Always Say What You Want
items.titleSort: You Kent Always Say What You Want

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E01. He Loves To Fly And He D'oh's.mp4
items.summary: Homer falls in love with private planes after taking a flight to Chicago with Mr. Burns. So Marge hires Homer a "life manager" to help him think positively and find a job that will allow him to fly for a living.
items.title: He Loves to Fly and He D'ohs
items.titleSort: He Loves to Fly and He D'ohs

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E02. The Homer Of Seville.mp4
items.summary: A freak accident gives Homer an operatic singing voice, and he becomes a star at the Springfield Opera. But with fame and fortune comes a price: He's continually bothered by fans, an obsessed woman in particular.
items.title: The Homer of Seville

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E03. Midnight Towboy.mp4
items.summary: Homer gets a tow-truck and becomes power drunk with impounding everybody's cars. The townsfolk set him up so that he antagonizes Louie,the tow-truck driver from Guidopolis,who imprisons him in his cellar,along with other over-reaching drivers. Fortunately for Homer,Maggie has learnt to be super-independent and rides to the rescue.
items.title: Midnight Towboy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E04. I Don't Wanna Know Why The Caged Bird Sings.mp4
items.summary: Bank robber Dwight agrees to give himself up if Marge visits him in prison but she chickens out so,when he escapes from jail,he comes after her and gets her to take him to the theme park where his real mother abandoned him. And whilst there he does a very brave deed,so that Marge is only too happy to visit him back inside. But he wants one more thing from her.
items.title: I Don't Wanna Know Why the Caged Bird Sings
items.titleSort: I Don't Wanna Know Why the Caged Bird Sings

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E05. Treehouse Of Horror Xviii.mp4
items.summary: In "ET: Go Home," Bart finds Kodos in the back yard and they become friends. However, Kodos has plans of killing everyone. In "Mr. and Mrs. Simpson," Homer and Marge discover that they are both expert assassins and try to kill each other. In "Heck House," Bart, Milhouse, Nelson, and Lisa pull pranks on Springfield residents while trick-or-treating, and are subjected to the wrath of Ned Flanders and his 'Heck House.'
items.title: Treehouse of Horror XVIII

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E06. Little Orphan Millie.mp4
items.summary: Milhouse stays with the Simpsons when his parents remarry each other and honeymoon on a cruise ship. But when his parents are knocked overboard and lost at sea, Milhouse decides to grow up and be a man.
items.title: Little Orphan Millie

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E07. Husbands And Knives.mp4
items.summary: Marge opens a gym for real women because she's disenchanted with Springfield's snooty, glitzy L.A. Body Works. Her gym, Shapes: A Gym for Women, is a huge success, launching a chain that makes Marge rich and famous. But Homer fears Marge will leave him for someone more attractive and goes to extreme lengths to try to save his marriage.
items.title: Husbands and Knives

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E08. Funeral For A Fiend.mp4
items.summary: Sideshow Bob tries again for revenge against the Simpsons.
items.title: Funeral for a Fiend

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E09. Eternal Moonshine Of The Simpson Mind.mp4
items.summary: Homer loses his memory--and his family--when he drinks Moe's most potent libation, the Forget-Me-Shot, in an episode that spoofs "Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind" and "It's a Wonderful Life."
items.title: Eternal Moonshine of the Simpson Mind
items.titleSort: Eternal Moonshine of the Simpson Mind

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E10. E Pluribus Wiggum.mp4
items.summary: Homer burns down Springfield's fast-food district. In order to float a bond issue to rebuild it, Mayor Quimby moves up election day, making Springfield's primary election the first in the nation. This causes the town to be overrun with reporters, candidates and pundits.
items.title: E Pluribus Wiggum

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E11. That 90's Show.mp4
items.summary: Flashbacks follow Marge and Homer back to their dating days, when she was a college student and he was working for his father to support her. Then Marge becomes smitten with a professor, so a sorrowful Homer turns to music--and invents grunge.
items.title: That 90's Show

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E12. Love, Springfieldian Style.mp4
items.summary: Homer and Marge celebrate Valentine's Day by going on the Tunnel of Love ride at a carnival, but they end up stranded when Bart pulls a prank involving gelatin. To pass the time, Homer tells the love story of Bonnie and Clyde, Marge tells her version of "Lady and the Tramp," and Bart tells the love story of Sid Vicious and Nancy Spungen.
items.title: Love, Springfieldian Style

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E13. The Debarted.mp4
items.summary: A new kid at school named Donny works with Bart on his pranks. But when the pranks start to backfire, Bart wonders if he can trust his new accomplice. Meanwhile, the Simpsons get a fancy loaner car after Marge gets in an accident, and Homer falls in love with it.
items.title: The Debarted

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E14. Dial 'n' For Nerder.mp4
items.summary: One of Bart's pranks results in Martin's death, but Lisa doesn't want him to confess because she would be considered an accomplice. Marge hires a television crew to find out if Homer is cheating on his diet.
items.title: Dial 'N' for Nerder

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E15. Smoke On The Daughter.mp4
items.summary: With Lisa's encouragement, Marge pursues her dream of becoming a ballerina. But when Marge auditions at the ballet academy, Lisa is invited to enroll. Unfortunately, Lisa becomes addicted to secondhand smoke from the other dancers. Meanwhile, Homer's beef-jerky operation runs into a snag.
items.title: Smoke on the Daughter

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E16. Papa Don't Leech.mp4
items.summary: The Simpsons take in a country singer Homer used to manage who owes back taxes to Springfield. She is now destitute, so the family tries to help her get back on her feet.
items.title: Papa Don't Leech

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E17. Apocalypse Cow.mp4
items.summary: Bart joins the 4-H club and raises a calf to be a blue-ribbon-winning bull, but panics when he learns the bull will be slaughtered.
items.title: Apocalypse Cow

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E18. Any Given Sundance.mp4
items.summary: Lisa makes a film about her family that gets accepted by the Sundance Film Festival, and the Simpsons go to Park City, Utah, to attend.
items.title: Any Given Sundance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E19. Mona Leaves-a.mp4
items.summary: Homer's mother, Mona, returns, but Homer is reluctant to trust her because she abandoned him so many times as a child.
items.title: Mona Leaves-a

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 19/S19E20. All About Lisa.mp4
items.summary: Lisa receives Springfield's Entertainer of the Year Award, and Sideshow Mel narrates her history in showbiz in a wry spoof of "All About Eve."
items.title: All About Lisa

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E01. Sex, Pies And Idiot Scrapes.mp4
items.summary: Bounty hunter Ned is forced to scrap his partnership with Homer when the hapless layabout skips bail, and Marge mistakenly takes a job at an erotic bakery.
items.title: Sex, Pies and Idiot Scrapes

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E02. Lost Verizon.mp4
items.summary: Bart lands himself in trouble when he steals a mobile phone from Denis Leary and subsequently uses it to land the actor a comical film role. The troublemaker then leads his family to the ancient ruins of Machu Picchu after Marge confiscates the device and decides to use its GPS technology to track her son.
items.title: Lost Verizon

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E03. Double, Double, Boy In Trouble.mp4
items.summary: An irreverent take on the Prince and the Pauper. Bart enthusiastically trades lives with a wealthy lookalike after landing himself in trouble for triggering a rampage of vacuum cleaners, but finds the lavish lifestyle too much when he becomes the target of all his new friends' pranks.
items.title: Double, Double, Boy in Trouble

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E04. Treehouse Of Horror Xix.mp4
items.summary: Springfield is the setting for parodies of Charlie Brown, It's the Great Pumpkin and Michael Bay's Transformers as Homer's vote on election day is misread by a renegade machine.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror XIX

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E05. Dangerous Curves.mp4
items.summary: Homer and Marge remember the ups and downs of their marriage through a series of flashbacks, including the time they each began flirting with guests at a glamorous party - a situation that led to a food fight and an unexpected swim in the pool.
items.title: Dangerous Curves

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E06. Homer And Lisa Exchange Cross Words.mp4
items.summary: Lisa learns she is good at crossword puzzles and enters a city-wide contest. Homer discovers he has a flair for letting loved ones down so he opens Sweet Conclusions Break-Up Service, but lands himself in trouble with his daughter when he places a bet against her in the competition.
items.title: Homer and Lisa Exchange Cross Words
items.titleSort: Homer and Lisa Exchange Cross Words

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E07. Mypods And Boomsticks.mp4
items.summary: Homer comes to the conclusion that the family of Bart's new Muslim friend are terrorists who are secretly plotting to blow up Springfield Mall. Meanwhile, Lisa learns about fiscal responsibility when she gets her own Mypod ... and eventually, a $1,200 bill.
items.title: Mypods and Boomsticks

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E08. The Burns And The Bees.mp4
items.summary: Mr Burns wins a professional basketball team in a poker game at the annual billionaire's retreat. He decides to build a state-of-the-art facility in an attempt to lure fans, but the stadium site is on the last remaining bee colony in Springfield - prompting Lisa to lead a protest.
items.title: The Burns and the Bees

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E09. Lisa The Drama Queen.mp4
items.summary: Lisa lets her imagination run wild when she makes a new friend and they create a magical kingdom together called Equalia, complete with characters and plotlines. But they find themselves facing a nightmare when the boundaries between reality and fantasy are blurred. With the voice of Emily Blunt.
items.title: Lisa the Drama Queen

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E10. Take My Life, Please.mp4
items.summary: Homer is jealous when old classmate Vance Connor is inducted into the Springfield Walk of Fame. Lenny and Carl confess they fixed the result in favor of Principal Dondelinger - leading the hapless father to speculate on how his life would have changed had he won the ballot.
items.title: Take My Life, Please

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E11. How The Test Was Won.mp4
items.summary: Bart gets a perfect score on a practice test for a national achievement test, which not only rattles Lisa, but it means Bart gets to attend a special party instead of having to take the actual test. Meanwhile, Homer must avoid injuring himself for an entire afternoon after failing to pay his insurance.
items.title: How the Test Was Won

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E12. No Loan Again, Naturally.mp4
items.summary: When the adjustable rate on the Simpson couple's mortgage resets at more than the pair can afford, they must sell their house. Good Samaritan Ned Flanders buys the house and rents it out to them at an affordable rate. But Homer pushes his luck too far when he takes advantage of Ned's generous landlord duties.
items.title: No Loan Again, Naturally

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E13. Gone Maggie Gone.mp4
items.summary: Lisa infiltrates a convent in order to steal back Maggie who was accidentally taken in by nuns. While in the convent, Lisa uncovers a series of cryptic clues leading to a hidden jewel in Springfield. With help from resident history buffs Principal Skinner and Comic Book Guy, Lisa sets off to find the coveted prize. But Springfield's Freemasons are also hot on the trail of the jewel, and Lisa must race against them to find the jewel and rescue Maggie.
items.title: Gone Maggie Gone

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E14. In The Name Of The Grandfather.mp4
items.summary: The Simpsons travel to Ireland so that Grampa can have a final drink at O'Flanagan's Pub - an old watering hole of his. But when the small town of Dunkilderry isn't quite what Grampa remembers it as, and O'Flanagans has become a rundown and empty pub, he and Homer decide to buy it and fix it up.
items.title: In the Name of the Grandfather
items.titleSort: In the Name of the Grandfather

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E15. Wedding For Disaster.mp4
items.summary: After Marge and Homer's marriage turns out to be invalid, they decide to re-do their vows. But when Homer goes missing, Bart and Lisa smell something funny and investigate his disappearance.
items.title: Wedding for Disaster

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E16. Eeny Teeny Maya Moe.mp4
items.summary: Moe once again searches for love and falls for a woman named Maya over the Internet. However, when Moe meets Maya face-to-face, he discovers it's more like face-to-knee, as Maya is only three feet tall.
items.title: Eeny Teeny Maya Moe

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E17. The Good, The Sad And The Drugly.mp4
items.summary: Bart gets Milhouse to take the rap for a prank at school, and then blows him off when he falls for a cute 5th grade do-gooder, prompting Milhouse's wrath. Meanwhile, Lisa begins taking "happy pills" to improve her negative outlook.
items.title: The Good, the Sad and the Drugly
items.titleSort: Good, the Sad and the Drugly

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E18. Father Knows Worst.mp4
items.summary: Bart and Lisa start struggling in their academic and social lives at school and Homer starts monitoring them and forcing them to do better. Meanwhile, Marge discovers a sauna in the basement.
items.title: Father Knows Worst

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E19. Waverly Hills 9021-d'oh.mp4
items.summary: When Marge learns Springfield Elementary is the worst school in the state, she and Homer rent an apartment in the upscale Waverly Hills school district so Bart and Lisa can attend a better school. Meanwhile, Homer moves into the rented Waverly Hills apartment and gets used to the bachelor lifestyle.
items.title: Waverly Hills 9-0-2-1-D'oh

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E20. Four Great Women And A Manicure.mp4
items.summary: Marge and Lisa visit the nail salon where they engage in a spirited debate as to whether a woman can be smart, powerful and beautiful all at the same time and spin four tales of famous women featuring famous Springfield faces: Selma as Queen Elizabeth I, Lisa as Snow White, Marge as Lady Macbeth and Maggie as Howard Roark, the idealistic architect protagonist from Ayn Randâ€™s The Fountainhead.
items.title: Four Great Women and a Manicure
items.titleSort: Four Great Women and a Manicure

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 20/S20E21. Coming To Homerica.mp4
items.summary: When nearby Ogdenvilleâ€™s economy crumbles due to tainted barley discovered in Krustyâ€™s veggie burgers, the unemployed workers of Ogdenville flock to Springfield. After Mayor Quimby closes Springfieldâ€™s borders and enlists private citizens to help patrol them, Homer organizes a border patrol group.
items.title: Coming to Homerica

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 21/S21E01. Homer The Whopper.mp4
items.summary: Homer gets the lead in a movie about a superhero who can take on the powers of every superhero in any comic book he touches. To whip Homer into superhero shape, the studio hires a celebrity fitness trainer.
items.title: Homer the Whopper

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 21/S21E02. Bart Gets A 'z'.mp4
items.summary: The fourth grade students of Springfield Elementary School decide to spike Ms. Krabappel's coffee in order to teach her a lesson after she takes away their cell phones. She is fired by Principal Skinner, who hires a new teacher named Zachary Vaughn. Although Vaughn is a hip young teacher who impresses the students, Bart is plagued by guilt and tries to get Ms. Krabappel hired back.
items.title: Bart Gets a 'Z'

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 21/S21E03. The Great Wife Hope.mp4
items.summary: The men and boys of Springfield become obsessed with Mixed Martial Arts, a violent sport where fighters inflict severe pain on one another. When Marge and her friends stage a protest, the show's promoter embraces the controversy and challenges Marge to a match, promising to shut down the competition if she wins.
items.title: The Great Wife Hope

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 21/S21E04. Treehouse Of Horror XX.mp4
items.summary:
Dial "M" for Murder or Press "#" to Return to Main Menu- Lisa is forced into a Hitchcockian murder scheme by Bart.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 21/S21E09. Thursdays With Abie.mp4
items.summary: Grampa is sitting on a bench waiting for his family when a thoughtful-looking man named Marshall Goldman approaches him and asks to hear about his life. Grampa tells Goldman about the time he was on a World War II battleship, which was hit by an enemy torpedo, and Goldman, a human-interest columnist, publishes it in The Springfield Shopper. Later, Grampa meets Mitch Albom and shares another story with Goldman for a follow-up article. Homer becomes jealous of Grampa's newfound fame and seeks a surrogate father. But when Homer discovers a draft of Goldman's third story, he must race to find Grampa before it is published and his life is changed forever.

The situation gets more complicated when Krusty and Penelope fall in love and decide to get married. Meanwhile, Homer, Lenny, and Carl consider working at a competing nuclear plant when Mr. Burns cuts off their daily doughnut service.

items.titleSort: Once Upon a Time in Springfield

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 21/S21E11. Million Dollar Maybe.mp4

When Bart finds out, he and Homer spend the money like itâ€™s going out of style, including buying front-row to tickets to see Coldplay in concert.

Team Springfield claims the win and moves on to the 2010 Vancouver Games where Bob Costas covers the action. items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 21/S21E17. American History X-cellent.mp4

items.summary: Homer is completing his court-ordered community service when he befriends his supervisor, Chief Wiggum, by offering him one of his sandwiches. They continue to grow close, but when the Chief gets injured during a botched bank robbery, Homer doesn't come through when Wiggum needs him the most. items.summary: The Simpsons decide to embrace a cheaper, alternate source of energy by erecting a wind turbine in their backyard. Meanwhile, a storm erupts, trapping a magnificent 150-foot-long blue whale ashore, and Lisa and Homer attempt to help the poor creature.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 21/S21E20. To Surveil With Love.mp4
items.summary: A bomb squad mistakenly blows up Homer's unattended gym bag, releasing radiation into the city and authorities react by suspending civil liberties. items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E04. Gone Abie Gone.mp4
items.summary: When Grandpa absconds from the retirement home the Simpsons follow a trail to a former night-spot where they learn that Grandpa was once a talented song writer and pianist, who, after Mona's departure, married singer Rita La Fleur but eschewed a musical career with her to look after Homer. The family locate her for a reconciliation whilst Lisa becomes addicted to online poker and almost loses her college fund though Bart saves the day.
items.title: Gone Abie Gone

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E05. Penny Wiseguys.mp4
items.summary: Homer is shocked to discover that his bowling teammate is an accountant for Fat Tony and his mob. When Fat Tony gets jury duty, he appoints Dan as the temporary don of the mafia. Meanwhile, Lisa adds insects to her vegetarian diet after she passes out in the middle of a saxophone solo, but starts questioning her decision when bugs start pleading for mercy in her dreams.
items.title: Penny-Wiseguys

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E06. A Tree Grows In Springfield.mp4
items.summary: Homer wins a MyPad at the school auction and Steve Mobbs, who is now in heaven, talks to Homer through it. Homer goes into a funk when he breaks the myPad, until Ned Flanders discovers a miracle tree in the Simpsons' back garden.
items.title: A Tree Grows in Springfield

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E07. The Day The Earth Stood Cool.mp4
items.summary: Homer is delighted to meet doughnut salesman Terrence and his wife Emily, the trendiest, hippest people in town who move in next door. Soon the whole of Springfield has been won over by their 'coolness' - except sensible Marge, who takes issue with Emily over breast-feeding. However when Bart and Terrence's son T-Rex start a fire which threatens the trendies' house it is Marge to the rescue with her 'old-fashioned' remedy.
items.title: The Day the Earth Stood Cool

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E08. To Cur With Love.mp4
items.summary: Grampa has to move into the Simpsons house following a fire at the retirement home, and on moving day, Homer 'throws his back out' and 'rests' at home. He later finds an advert for a video game, Villageville on his myPad, and starts playing. During that time, Homer loses Santa's Little Helper. When the family find him, Homer doesn't seem to care because he's "not a dog person". Grampa later tells the rest of the family the story of Homer's childhood companion, pet dog Bongo.
items.title: To Cur, with Love

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E09. Homer Goes To Prep School.mp4
items.summary: Homer joins the "Springfield Preppers," an off-the-grid survivalist group whose leader has set up a top-secret retreat outside of town to prepare for the end of the world.
items.title: Homer Goes to Prep School

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E10. A Test Before Trying.mp4
items.summary: Following appalling grades the school is threatened with closure and the pupils dispersed until it is discovered that Bart has yet to sit his exam, which, if he passes, will save the school's future. He is very nervous but, with the accidental help of his pet beetle, manages to make the grade. Homer meanwhile discovers a parking meter, which he uses illegally to make money until Marge makes him donate the profits to a good cause.
items.title: A Test Before Trying

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E11. The Changing Of The Guardian.mp4
items.summary: A tornado touches down in Springfield which sucks up Santa's Little Helper. While Homer and Marge are out looking for the family dog, the tornado strikes again and almost takes Marge and Homer. Marge is distraught about the kids and decide to pick a  guardian to care for the children.
items.title: The Changing of the Guardian

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E12. Love Is A Many Splintered Thing.mp4
items.summary: Bart's dream girl, Mary Spuckler, comes to town, but his failure to pay her enough attention is having a negative impact on their relationship. Meanwhile, Homer once again runs afoul of Marge and lands in the doghouse.
items.title: Love Is a Many-Splintered Thing

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E13. Hardly Kirk-ing.mp4
items.summary: When Marge bans the family from watching television for a day Homer becomes addicted to a children's puzzle book whilst Bart dresses Milhouse up to look like his father so that they can rent a van, buy alcohol and vote. They also wander into a sales promotion where the saleswoman becomes very attracted to Milhouse though Marge and Homer arrive in time to take the kids home.
items.title: Hardly Kirk-ing

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E14. Gorgeous Grampa.mp4
items.summary: Homer's obsession with the TV show "Storage Battles" leads the family to discover Grampa's past identity as "Gorgeous Godfrey," the most feared, villainous man in pro-wrestling history
items.title: Gorgeous Grampa

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E15. Blake-eyed Please.mp4
items.summary: When Flanders' parents prove to prefer Homer's company to his, he jealously responds by giving Homer a shiner, and then tries desperately to reconcile with him. Meanwhile, Lisa is at a loss to understand why a new substitute teacher is bullying her for no obvious reason.
items.title: Black-Eyed, Please

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E16. Dark Knight Court.mp4
items.summary: Springfield's Easter is ruined by a prank and all fingers point to Bart. It is up to Lisa to save her brother, in a student court presided over by Attorney General Janet Reno. Meanwhile, inspired by an old comic book, Mr. Burns becomes an ineffectual superheroâ€”fruit bat man.
items.title: Dark Knight Court

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E17. What Animated Women Want.mp4
items.summary: Homer's behavior once again lands him in hot water with Marge and he needs to fathom a way to save his marriage, while a dose of "A Streetcar Named Desire" drives Milhouse to affect a Marlon Brando-esque bad-boy demeanor in an effort to impress Lisa.
items.title: What Animated Women Want

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E18. Pulpit Friction.mp4
items.summary: Following an infestation of bugs the Simpsons send their clothes to be dry-cleaned but Marge's wedding dress ends up with Krusty and Lisa plays sleuth to get it back. Meanwhile trendy new vicar Elijah Hooper appoints Homer as a deacon, causing Tim Lovejoy to resign and Bart and Milhouse to join forces with Ned Flanders to restore the old order - helped by the bugs.
items.title: Pulpit Friction

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E19. Whiskey Business.mp4
items.summary: Moe is flying high after venture capitalists take a shine to his homemade whiskey, while Grampa, after injuring himself babysitting Bart, decides he'd rather be looked after by his grandson than be at the nursing home. Also, Lisa voices her displeasure at a hologram of music legend Bleeding Gums Murphy, and Sonny Rollins (as himself) shows up to ask her to stop all that jazz about boycotting a record label.
items.title: Whiskey Business

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E20. The Fabulous Faker Boy.mp4
items.summary: Marge encourages Bart to explore his creative side, and his initial reticence quickly subsides when she hires Slavaâ€™s beautiful daughter, Zhenya, as his new piano instructor. Homer is shocked when he loses the last two hairs on his head, and employs a wide variety of headgear to try and keep his new found baldness a secret from Marge.
items.title: The Fabulous Faker Boy

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E21. The Saga Of Carl.mp4
items.summary: Homer, Moe, Lenny and Carl win $200,000 in the Springfield Lottery. But when Carl takes off to Iceland â€“ his homeland â€“ with all the winnings, the guys embark on a Nordic adventure to get the cash back.
items.title: The Saga of Carl

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 24/S24E22. Dangers On A Train.mp4
items.summary: When Marge tries to buy Homer snack cakes for their anniversary, she winds up meeting a married man who shares a common love of British Television. Ignorant of all, Homer attempts to secretly construct a romantic anniversary train in the Simpsons back yard.
items.title: Dangers on a Train

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E01. Homerland.mp4
items.summary: A parody of "Homeland". Homer starts to act strangely polite after returning from a nuclear power plant convention, prompting a suspicious Lisa to ask an intense FBI agent named Annie (Kristen Wiig) to help her solve this mystery.
items.title: Homerland

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E02. Treehouse Of Horror Xxiv.mp4
items.summary: The scariest Simpsons Halloween show yet, featuring an opening by Guillermo Del Toro.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror XXIV

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E03. Four Regrettings And A Funeral.mp4
items.summary: Kent Brockman has decided that local news has been a real mistake and a terrible career move for him.
items.title: Four Regrettings and a Funeral

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E04. Yolo.mp4
items.summary: Marge encourages Homer to cross an item off an old to-do list by inviting an old pen pal to visit; Lisa institutes an honor code at school.
items.title: YOLO

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E05. Labor Pains.mp4
items.summary: Homer remembers his Lamaze skills when he's forced to deliver a baby in an elevator. When the mother names the child Homer Jr., he quickly develops a deep emotional bond with the kid. Meanwhile, Lisa is recruited by the cheerleaders of the local pro football team, the Springfield Atoms.
items.title: Labor Pains

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E06. The Kid Is All Right.mp4
items.summary: A new student comes to Springfield Elementary called Isabel Gutierrez, who is Lisa's intellectual equal. Lisa and Isabel become fast best friends but things take a left turn when they realize they have different political views - Isabel is a republican. They end up running against each other in the second-grade election, and then we flash to the future where they're engaged in an actual presidential debate - and Anderson Cooper is the moderator.
items.title: The Kid Is All Right

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E07. Yellow Subterfuge.mp4
items.summary: Principal Skinner promises the students that the best-behaved among them can take a ride in a submarine. When Skinner gives all the kids a clean slate, Bart believes even his own past indiscretions will be forgotten if he doesnâ€™t get into any more trouble. Meanwhile Lisa tries to help a cash-poor Krusty to turn things around by suggesting he sell the foreign rights to his shows.
items.title: Yellow Subterfuge

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E08. White Christmas Blues.mp4
items.summary: Springfield is inundated with holiday revelers after the nuclear power plant springs a radiation leak, causing snow to fall all over town. When the tourists drive up Christmas shopping prices, Marge opens up the Simpsons' house to boarders.
items.title: White Christmas Blues

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E09. Steal This Episode.mp4
items.summary: Homer becomes annoyed with movie theaters, so Bart teaches him how to download movies illegally. Homer is delighted with his discovery of free movies until he's caught for piracy. Deputy Director Gratman, the FBI's anti-piracy boss, is tasked with hunting down Homer, who stands accused of illegally downloading a film.
items.title: Steal This Episode

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E10. Married To The Blob.mp4
items.summary: The Android's Dungeon owner falls for Kumiko, a Japanese woman who shares his interest in comics and, advised by the Simpsons, he starts to date her. Then her father arrives from Japan and insists she return home with him. Homer takes him out for a night on the town where, after consuming large quantities of the hallucination-inducing snake rice wine, the father comes to perceive reality through fantasy and permits the couple to marry.
items.title: Married to the Blob

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E11. Specs And The City.mp4
items.summary: Mr. Burns' Christmas present to his employees, a pair of augmented reality glasses, places a strain on Homer and Marge's relationship. Meanwhile, Bart wrestles with giving a Valentine's Day card to Nelson.
items.title: Specs and the City

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E12. Diggs.mp4
items.summary: A recent transfer student named Diggs rescues Bart from a confrontation with bullies.
items.title: Diggs

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E13. The Man Who Grew Too Much.mp4
items.summary: During a research trip, Lisa learns that Sideshow Bob is the chief scientist at a big chemical engineering company; Marge tries to teach a teen church group about healthy sexual practices.
items.title: The Man Who Grew Too Much

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E14. The Winter Of His Content.mp4
items.summary: When Abe and two of his friends move in with the Simpsons after the Springfield Retirement Castle closes, Homer begins to embrace their lifestyle. Meanwhile, Nelson initiates Bart into the bully group after coming to his defense.
items.title: The Winter of His Content

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E15. The War Of Art.mp4
items.summary: After Lisa's new pet guinea pig destroys the Simpsons' living room art, Marge finds a beautiful painting at the Van Houten's yard sale, which Homer snaps up for 20 bucks
items.title: The War of Art

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E16. You Don T Have To Live Like A Referee.mp4
items.summary: Homer is recruited as a World Cup referee after Lisa extols his integrity on the youth soccer field in a Springfield Elementary speech contest. But when the Simpsons travel to Brazil (again), Homer finds his honesty tested by one of South America's slickest gangsters in the soccer match-bribing business.
items.title: You Don't Have to Live Like a Referee
items.titleSort: You Don't Have to Live Like a Referee

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E17. Luca$.mp4
items.summary: Lisa dates a competitive eater; Bart benefits from helping convict Snake Jailbird escape from a jam.
items.title: Luca$

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E18. Days Of Future Future.mp4
items.summary: Set in the future, Homer has a new clone for every time he dies. Lisa is married to a zombie version of Milhouse, while Bart deals with custody issues with his ex-wife, Jenda. Each defines what love means to them.
items.title: Days of Future Future

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E19. What To Expect When Bart's Expecting.mp4
items.summary: When Bart's voodoo doll spell accidentally makes his teacher pregnant, he becomes a savior to couples hoping to conceive.
items.title: What to Expect When Bart's Expecting
items.titleSort: What to Expect When Bart's Expecting

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E20. Brick Like Me.mp4
items.summary: Homer wakes up in a Springfield where everyone and everything is made out of Legos, and he must figure his way out before he gets stuck in the plastic world forever.
items.title: Brick Like Me

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E21. Pay Pal.mp4
items.summary: Marge swears off befriending any more couples when Homer offends their charming new British neighbors, but when Lisa declares that she, too, doesnâ€™t need friends, Marge reconsiders.
items.title: Pay Pal

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 25/S25E22. The Yellow Badge Of Cowardge.mp4
items.summary: Bart feels guilty after he wins the annual "last day of school" race around Springfield Elementary School, with help from Nelson, who beats up the frontrunner, Milhouse. Meanwhile, Homer tries to bring back 4th of July fireworks after they are canceled due to budget cuts.
items.title: The Yellow Badge of Cowardge

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E01. Clown In The Dumps.mp4
items.summary: A Springfield resident dies, Krusty retires after he's offended by a comedy cable channel roast of him, and Lisa tries to protect Homer from getting hurt.
items.title: Clown in the Dumps

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E02. The Wreck Of The Relationship.mp4
items.summary: When Bart disrespects Homer's authority, Homer makes a point to try his hand at parenting. This proves fruitless, so Marge signs them up for the Relation Ship, where they'll resolve their conflicts at sea. Meanwhile, Marge is in charge of Homer's fantasy football league, but manages to win despite being the underdog.
items.title: The Wreck of the Relationship

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E03. Super Franchise Me.mp4
items.summary: Marge opens a sandwich franchise store after her sandwiches become a huge hit at Springfield Elementary. But running day-to-day at the store proves challenging, especially when the same franchise opens another location across the street.
items.title: Super Franchise Me

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E04. Treehouse Of Horror Xxv.mp4
items.summary: In a Halloween-theme episode Bart reads Aramaic symbols from the bottom of his desk and he and Lisa are transported to an alternate world filled with demons. Also, Moe organizes a "Clockwork Orange"-ish gang in which member Dum (Homer) falls for a young lady (Marge) who wants him to quit. In a homage to "The Others," the Simpsons reconnect with their earlier incarnations from the Tracey Ullman era.
items.title: Treehouse of Horror XXV

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E05. Opposites A-frack.mp4
items.summary: Lisa brings in assembly woman Maxine Lombard to put a stop to Mr. Burns' fracking operation, but is taken aback when the two political opponents find themselves attracted to one another.
items.title: Opposites A-Frack

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E06. Simpsorama.mp4
items.summary: The Planet Express crew come to present-day Springfield to prevent the Simpsons from destroying the future.
items.title: Simpsorama

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E07. Blazed And Confused.mp4
items.summary: When Edne Krabapple's (Marcia Wallace) replacement, a sadistic temporary teacher Jack Lassen (Willem Dafoe) gives Bart a humiliating haircut, Bart plans revenge. His opportunity comes when he discovers that Lassen is about to light the Blazing Guy (an apparent parody of burning man) effigy at a hippie camp-site. He contrives to get the family on holiday there and to wreck Lassen's big moment.
items.title: Blazed and Confused

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E08. Covercraft.mp4
items.summary: Homer has a mid-life crisis, takes up bass guitar and forms a cover band with some of the other dads in town. But the band's modest early success is soon overwhelmed by the breakout potential of their most unlikely star, Apu.
items.title: Covercraft

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E09. I Won't Be Home For Christmas.mp4
items.summary: After Moe convinces Homer to stay out drinking on Christmas Eve, Marge tells Homer not to come home. This leads to Homer's sad trek through lonely Springfield, where he learns that the only place where one should truly get drunk on Christmas is home.
items.title: I Won't Be Home for Christmas
items.titleSort: I Won't Be Home for Christmas

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E10. The Man Who Came To Be Dinner.mp4
items.summary: During a trip to "Dizzneeland" the Simpsons board the wrong ride, Rocket To Your Doom, and are transported through the galaxy to Kang and Kodos' home planet, where they are held captive at the local zoo and the inhabitants decide to eat Homer.
items.title: The Man Who Came to Be Dinner
items.titleSort: Man Who Came to Be Dinner

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E11. Bart's New Friend.mp4
items.summary: Bart has a new accomplice and best friend when Homer is hypnotized at the circus and believes he is a young boy again.
items.title: Bart's New Friend

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E12. The Musk Who Fell To Earth.mp4
items.summary: When inventor Elon Musk lands in Springfield, he and Homer become fast friends and revolutionize the town's nuclear plant. But when Musk goes overboard and Mr. Burns wants him removed, Homer must figure out a way to break up with him.
items.title: The Musk Who Fell to Earth

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E13. Walking Big & Tall.mp4
items.summary: At a concert given by Bart and Lisa to perform Springfield's new anthem Homer has such trouble rising from his seat due to his weight that he injures several people. Marge sends him to a dieting club but instead he finds himself joining Wide Pride, a group that celebrates being large and which he totally embraces - until its leader has a fatal accident.
items.title: Walking Big & Tall

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E14. My Fare Lady.mp4
items.summary: When Marge gets fed up with the thankless duty of chauffeuring her kids around, she begins working as a driver for a transportation app service. Meanwhile, Homer bankrupts Moe when he watches over the bar for one night, which forces Moe to take a temporary job as a janitor at the nuclear plant.
items.title: My Fare Lady

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E15. The Princess Guide.mp4
items.summary: Homer is put in charge of keeping Princess Kemi out of trouble while her father, a Nigerian king, works out a uranium deal with Mr. Burns.
items.title: The Princess Guide

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E16. Sky Police.mp4
items.summary: Chief Wiggum is mistakenly delivered a military jet pack, which he gleefully accepts and uses in order to fight crime. But when the jet pack crashes into the church, the congregation, led by Marge, must resort to gambling and counting cards in order to collect money to repair the church.
items.title: Sky Police

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E17. Waiting For Duffman.mp4
items.summary: When Duffman (guest voice Stacy Keach) undergoes hip replacement surgery and retires, the company sets up a reality show competition to find his replacement. Homer wins the competition, and because the job requires him to stay sober, he learns that beer isn't as necessary as he thought to have a good time.
items.title: Waiting for Duffman

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E18. Peeping Mom.mp4
items.summary: Bart lies about being involved in a bulldozer crash, so Marge decides to follow him everywhere until he confesses. Meanwhile, Homer ignores Santaâ€™s Little Helper when Flanders gets a new dog.
items.title: Peeping Mom

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E19. The Kids Are All Fight.mp4
items.summary: Family photos from six years earlier show that Lisa and Bart were bitter rivals, always fighting each other. However, when they were left in the charge of Grandma Flanders, whom they thought had died, they left the house in search of ice cream and Bart saved Lisa's life - leading to the on and off relationship that they still have.
items.title: The Kids Are All Fight

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E20. Let's Go Fly A Coot.mp4
items.summary: Homer is arrested by the military after trying to sabotage expensive children's birthday parties and made to listen to his father recounting his days in the air force, where he broke the sound barrier and met his future wife. Bart takes up smoking electronic cigarettes to impress Milhouse's cousin, who is visiting from the Netherlands, but ultimately decides that she is not worth impressing.
items.title: Let's Go Fly a Coot

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E21. Bull-e.mp4
items.summary: After Bart gets bullied at the school dance, Marge convinces the town to pass anti-bullying legislation. Homer then gets arrested and sent to rehab for bullying Ned Flanders, only to subsequently leave rehab as a hero.
items.title: Bull-E

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 26/S26E22. Mathlete's Feat.mp4
items.summary: Lisa joins a maths quiz team, who fare poorly against rivals who have superior technology. So Springfield goes totally digital, burning paper books . Unfortunately a meltdown means the entire system crashes but using decidedly old-fashioned methods Lisa builds up the quiz team and, with unlikely help from Bart, takes it to victory.
items.title: Mathlete's Feat

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 27/S27E01. Every Man's Dream.mp4
items.summary: Homer is diagnosed with narcolepsy, but instead of returning home with his prescription medication, he returns home drunk. He and Marge visit a marriage counselor and have a trial separation, during which Homer begins dating a 20-something.
items.title: Every Man's Dream

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 27/S27E02. Cue Detective.mp4
items.summary: Scotty Boom, a Chew Network super-chef, challenges Homer to a smoke-off. But when someone steals Homerâ€™s secret weapon â€“ a smoker he bought off a mysterious man at a BBQ shack â€“ Lisa and Bart are on the case.
items.title: Cue Detective

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 27/S27E03. Puffless.mp4
items.summary: Upon learning that their father really died of lung cancer, Selma and Patty agree to quit smoking. When Selma relapses, an angry Patty moves in with Marge and Homer.
items.title: Puffless

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 27/S27E04. Halloween Of Horror.mp4
items.summary: When Lisa becomes scared at the Krustyland Halloween Horror Night, Homer is forced to take down his Everscream Terrors decorations. Halloween pop-up employees seek vengeance on Homer for causing them to lose their jobs, and rob his house while Homer and Lisa hide out in the attic. Homer and Lisa light up their stored holiday decorations to attract attention and stand up to the intruders.
items.title: Halloween of Horror

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/The Simpsons/The Simpson's Season 27/S27E05. Treehouse Of Horror Xxvi.mp4
items.summary: In the annual fright fest Halloween episode, Sideshow Bob finally kills Bart, only to reanimate him; Homer wakes up with short-term memory loss; and Lisa, Bart, and Milhouse get super powers from radiation.

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (1987 Animated Series)/Season 1/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles - 1x01 - Turtle Tracks   [DarkDream].mkv
items.summary: April O'Neil, ace reporter for Channel 6, investigates recent break-ins, allegedly by Ninjas, which have resulted in the thefts of numerous technologies. A chance encounter with a gang of thieves soon leads her to a bigger story when she is saved from the criminals by four Ninja trained, mutated Turtles.
items.title: Turtle Tracks

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (1987 Animated Series)/Season 1/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles - 1x02 - Enter The Shredder   [DarkDream].mkv
items.summary: The Shredder kidnaps Splinter in an attempt to lure the Turtles to his own cause. In order to rescue Splinter the Turtles must enter the Shredder's mobile fortress and brave it's dangerous weaponry.
items.title: Enter: The Shredder

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (1987 Animated Series)/Season 1/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles - 1x03 - A Thing About Rats   [DarkDream].mkv
items.summary: Baxter Stockman, a mad scientist, is showing an exterminator his new invention: a rat catching robot called Mousers.
items.title: A Thing about Rats

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (1987 Animated Series)/Season 1/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles - 1x04 - Hot Rodding Teenagers From Dimension X   [DarkDream].mkv
items.summary: Shredder experiments with the Inter-Dimensional Portal, hoping to contact Krangs' Rock Soldiers and prepare an invasion of Earth, but a group of fun-loving aliens called the Neutrionos, renegades in Krang's dimension, take advantage of the Portal's opening and use it to arrive on Earth.
items.title: Hot Rodding Teenagers from Dimension X
items.titleSort: Hot Rodding Teenagers from Dimension X

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (1987 Animated Series)/Season 1/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles - 1x05 - Shredder & Splintered   [DarkDream].mkv
items.summary: As Shredder lures Splinter into he Technodrome, this time with the promise that a weapon in his possession can restore the sensei to human form, the Turtles confront a giant-sized Krang, now in a new body, in the heart of New York City.
items.title: Shredder & Splintered

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (1987 Animated Series)/Season 2/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles - 2x01 - Return Of The Shredder   [DarkDream].mkv
items.summary: Just when the Turtles believe themselves rid of Shredder, tin-grin is able to persuade Krang to return him to Earth.
items.title: Return of the Shredder

items.title: The Incredible Shrinking Turtles

items.titleSort: It Came from Beneath the Sewers

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (1987 Animated Series)/Season 2/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles - 2x04 - The Mean Machines   [DarkDream].mkv
items.summary: After the batteries died in the alien crystal converger, Donatello, using spare circuits from the space ship, builds a tracking device to help locate the second fragment of the Eye of Zarnov.
items.title: The Mean Machines

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles (1987 Animated Series)/Season 2/Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles - 2x05 - Curse Of The Evil Eye   [DarkDream].mkv

items.title: Curse of the Evil Eye

items.title: The Case of the Killer Pizzas

items.summary: The female X-Men are fed up with playing second fiddle, and form a vigilante crime-fighting group called the Bayville Sirens. Scott and Kurt try to figure out what they are up to until an old enemy crosses the Sirens' path.
items.title: Walk on the Wild Side

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S02/X-Men Evolution - S02 E14 - Retreat.avi
items.summary: Nick Fury informs Wolverine that Magneto has stolen a device once used to create Captain America. Wolverine, Rogue and Nightcrawler go to recover it. Meanwhile, Logan reminisces about his history with Captain America during World War II.
items.title: Operation: Rebirth

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S02/X-Men Evolution - S02 E15 - The HeX Factor.avi
items.summary: Mystique returns to the Brotherhood with a mentally unstable, but immensely powerful mutant named Wanda Maximoff who was abducted from a mental institution, much to the horror of her twin brother Pietro.
items.title: The HeX Factor

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S02/X-Men Evolution - S02 E16-17 - Day of Reckoning.avi
items.summary: At Xavier's urging, the Brotherhood and the X-Men unite to battle Magneto; and the Institute begins to self-destruct while students are trapped in the mansion.
items.title: Day of Reckoning (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E01 - Day of Recovery.avi
items.summary: X-Men and the Brotherhood deal with the aftermath of the world finding out about mutants. The Institute is blown up, and Mystique posed as Prof. X to blow it up. Some of the X-Men and Brotherhood are captured, leaving the mutants that escaped to find them and the Professor.
items.title: Day of Recovery

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E02 - The Stuff of Heroes.avi
items.summary: Rogue and Wolverine duck a squad of soldiers when the nationwide alert goes out against mutants, while Storm and Beast go into a meeting of Congress to defend themselves. Meanwhile Juggernaut goes on a rampage and the X-Men feel obliged to take him down.
items.title: The Stuff of Heroes

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E03 - Mainstream.avi
items.summary: During the rebuilding of the manor, Kitty and Kurt intercept a bunch of graffiti artists disguised as monsters. The older students get to go back to Bayville High for one day before attending a hearing to determine their ultimate fate, while they are banned from using their powers.
items.title: Mainstream

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E04 - The Stuff of Villains.avi
items.summary: The Scarlet Witch wants to find out where her father Magneto is, so she enlists Caliban for help. She then goes to her brother Quicksilver for information. When he refuses, Wanda delivers him to the police to try drawing Magneto out.
items.title: The Stuff of Villains

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E05 - Blind Alley.avi
items.summary: Mystique escapes from imprisonment while the X-Men repair and rebuild the Institute. Disguised as Alex, she lures Scott into a trap - leaving him stranded in the middle of the Mexican desert without his glasses.
items.title: Blind Alley

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E06 - X-Treme Measures.avi
items.summary: Spyke joins a skateboarding contest sponsored by "Pow-R 8" soda. However, Pow-R 8 is harmful to mutants, and when Spyke drinks a swig, it causes serious side effects to his mutation. The mysterious Morlocks, step in to help him.
items.title: X-Treme Measures

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E07 - The Toad, the Witch, and the Wardrobe.avi
items.summary: Wanda receives a clue from one of Magneto's minions, Pyro, directing her to a ski resort. Meanwhile, Kurt is meeting Amanda's parents for the first time, and the Toad believes he can use Kurt's holo-inducer to disguise himself and win Wanda's love.
items.title: The Toad, The Witch, and The Wardrobe
items.titleSort: Toad, The Witch, and The Wardrobe

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E08 - Self Possessed.avi
items.summary: Rogue has absorbed so many thoughts, memories and personalities of other people that she can no longer contain or control them. She becomes completely overwhelmed when she accidentally touches Risty and learns the truth about her identity.
items.title: Self Possessed

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E09 - Under Lock and Key.avi
items.summary: Angel spots Gambit stealing a mysterious artifact, but when he tries to stop him, Mesmero fights him off. When the Acolytes want to steal another artifact, the X-Men fight them and discover there is a bigger plan happening.
items.title: Under Lock and Key

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E10 - Cruise Control.avi
items.summary: A mysterious female assassin terrorizes the X-Mansion, knocking out the X-Men one by one. Wolverine finds out that it is his clone, created by the Dr. Deborah Risman and raised without love by HYDRA, and she wants to kill him because she holds him responsible for her miserable life. Wolverine and X-23, as she is called, square off in a battle that Wolverine does not want to win.
items.title: X23

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E11 - X23.avi
items.summary: Rogue falls under the mind control of Mesmero and is used as a weapon to absorb the mutant abilities of every X-Man, Brotherhood, and Acolyte member. Mesmero wants Rogue to give all of her stolen abilities to Apocalypse to awaken him.
items.title: Dark Horizon (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S03/X-Men Evolution - S03 E12-13 - Dark Horizon.avi
items.summary: The X-Men, Brotherhood, and Acolytes continue their battle against Mesmero. The heroes and villains track down Apocalypse to Egypt, but only to come face-to-face with him and having failed to prevent Apocalypse from coming back to life.
items.title: Dark Horizon (2)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S04/X-Men Evolution - S04 E01 - Impact.avi
items.summary: A strange phenomena occurs in the wake of Apocalypse, and the X-Men receive permission from the government to study it. Meanwhile, Nightcrawler tries to revive his mother Mystique who is still trapped in stone, much to the dismay of Rogue.
items.title: Impact

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S04/X-Men Evolution - S04 E02 - No Good Deed.avi
items.summary: The Brotherhood cause mishaps so they can stop them and appear to be heroes.
items.title: No Good Deed

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S04/X-Men Evolution - S04 E03 - Target X.avi
items.summary: Wolverine finds his clone, X-23, who's trying to destroy Hydra, her creator, and the two team up to complete the mission.
items.title: Target X

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S04/X-Men Evolution - S04 E04 - Sins Of The Son.avi
items.summary: Xavier is told he has a son, who has been kidnapped in Scotland. So he and the X-Men head there to find him.
items.title: Sins of the Son

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S04/X-Men Evolution - S04 E05 - Uprising.avi
items.summary: Hate crimes against mutants in Bayville prompt Spyke to return to stop the violence.
items.title: Uprising

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S04/X-Men Evolution - S04 E06 - Cajun Spice.avi
items.summary: Rogue is kidnapped by Gambit, who says he's there to help her; and the X-Men search for her, led by Wolverine.
items.title: Cajun Spice

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S04/X-Men Evolution - S04 E07 - Ghost Of A Chance.avi
items.summary: Kitty is rescued by a mutant and invites her to join the institute. But the mutant soon vanishes, and only Kitty remembers her.
items.title: Ghost of a Chance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S04/X-Men Evolution - S04 E08 - Ascension (Part I).avi
items.summary: Xavier finds Apocalypse in Egypt, and Apocalypse unleashes four horsemen, who battle the X-Men.
items.title: Ascension (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men Evolution/S04/X-Men Evolution - S04 E09 - Ascension (Part II).avi
items.summary: In order to prevent all of humankind from being turned into mutants, the X-Men, the Brotherhood, S.H.I.E.L.D., The Acolytes, Angel, Spyke, Havok, and the New Mutants all join forces to save humanity from the ambitions of Apocalypse.
items.title: Ascension (2)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - PRYDE of The X-Men (Original 1989 Pilot - 480p SD)/X-Men - PRYDE of The X-Men (Original 1989 Pilot).avi
items.title: Episode 89

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E01 - Night Of The Sentinels (Part 1).mp4
items.summary: A young teenager has been rejecting her mutant powers ever since she discovered them. But when giant robots track her down, it's up to the X-Men to save her.
items.title: Night of the Sentinels (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E02 - Night Of The Sentinels (Part 2).mp4
items.summary: Breaking into the Mutant Control Agency's headquarters to destroy the registration files on mutants, the X-Men lose two of their members against the Sentinels, but eventually gain another.
items.title: Night of the Sentinels (2)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E03 - Enter Magneto.mp4
items.summary: As the Beast faces an arraignment in court before a mutant-hating public, the X-Men unwillingly take in an old enemy of Wolverine's. Magneto, an old friend turned enemy of Professor Xavier's, attacks a military base in an attempt to unite mutants against humanity.
items.title: Enter Magneto

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E04 - Deadly Reunions.mp4
items.summary: Professor Xavier and Magneto confront each other for the first time in years, meanwhile Wolverine and Sabretooth come face to face. Professor Xavier tries to examine Sabretooth's mind to figure out his rage problem. After his last terrorist action failed, Magneto plots a new one to bring Professor Xavier out into the open. Sabretooth and Wolverine confront each other in the mansion's war room.
items.title: Deadly Reunions

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E05 - Captive Hearts.mp4
items.summary: Wolverine must overcome his feelings for Jean, and Storm must overcome her crippling claustrophobia, when the team journeys into the sewer to rescue Jean Grey & Cyclops from a race of hideously deformed mutants known as Morlocks, and their leader Callisto, who wants to make Scott her king.
items.title: Captive Hearts

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E06 - Cold Vengeance.mp4
items.summary: Having left the X-Men to seek peace in the arctic, Wolverine instead finds himself battling Sabretooth for the safety of an Inuit tribe. Storm, Gambit, and Jubilee investigate an island resort which welcomes mutants, and might be too good to be true.
items.title: Cold Vengeance

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E07 - Slave Island.mp4
items.summary: Gambit, Storm, and Jubilee become slave labor on the island resort of Genosha, along with other mutants, forced to help build the new power source for a Sentinel factory. They're given aide in escaping by a mysterious mercenary named Cable.
items.title: Slave Island

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E08 - The Unstoppable Juggernaut.mp4
items.summary: The X-Men return from Genosha, finding the home destroyed, and Professor Xavier missing. They suspect a super-strong Russian mutant named Colossus, but the real culprit turns out to be someone more human, far tougher, and with deeper ties to the Professor.
items.title: The Unstoppable Juggernaut

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E09 - The Cure.mp4
items.summary: The same scientist who created the ability suppression collars for Genosha claims to have developed a cure for mutation. Rogue goes to the doctor for help. Professor Xavier has shown up at Muir Island to investigate the same "cure". They quickly find out that the doctor and his cure are not what she was lead to believe.
items.title: The Cure

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E10 - Come The Apocalypse.mp4
items.summary: Still posing as Dr. Adler, Mystique is still promising a cure for mutation, but little do they know that she's really recruiting mutants to become the Four Horsemen of Apocalypse. And Apocalypse's plans for "survival of the fittest" comes to light.
items.title: Come the Apocalypse

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E11 - Days Of Future Past (Part 1).mp4
items.summary: A mutant from more than half a century into the future, named Bishop, arrives in the present, attempting to change history for the better, by stopping an X-Man from committing an assassination. But between being chased by a future breed of Sentinel, and the details of his mission being fuzzy, he's got his work cut out for him.
items.title: Days of Future Past (1)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E12 - Days Of Future Past (Part 2).mp4
items.summary: Bishop believes that the assassin he's come back in time to stop is Gambit. The X-men go to Washington D.C. to try and stop the assassination themselves leaving Gambit and Bishop back at the mansion and Wolverine to keep an eye on them. Gambit takes off to Washington D.C. to prove he's not the assassin only to be confronted by... himself?
items.title: Days of Future Past (2)

items.locations: /volume1/PLEX_MEDIA/TV Shows/X-Men - The Animated Series/S01/X-Men T.A.S - S01 E13 - The Final Decision.mp4
items.summary: Prominent anti-mutant and presidential hopeful Senator Kelly is caught in a tug-of-war between Magneto's goal of mutant superiority, the X-Men's dream of peaceful co-existance between mutants and humans, and the mutant-hunting Sentinel robots' goals of global domination.
items.title: The Final Decision
